87, 0), (432664, 'Without failure there is no sweetness in success. There''s no understanding of it.', 2097, 0), (432665, 'We feel a lot of pressure about looking silly or appearing weak, whatever that means, or being a failure. You have to keep in your head: what''s the worst that can happen?', 55567, 0), (432666, 'I don''t understand a way to work other than bold-facedly running towards failure.', 66787, 0), (432667, 'The exposed nature of life in the public square affects leaders'' attitudes toward risk - and failure.', 68451, 0), (432668, 'Ambitious failure, magnificent failure, is a very good thing.', 5456, 0), (432669, 'I went to a motivational training course once, a course of self-discovery, and I found out after a week that my fear - it was not a fear of not being accepted - was a very violent fear of failure.', 68888, 0), (432670, 'I assume everything I do in life is gonna be a failure, and then if it turns up roses, then I''m psyched.', 68889, 0), (432671, 'Our nation''s Social Security Trust Fund is depleting at an alarming rate, and failure to implement immediate reforms endangers the ability of Americans to plan for their retirement with the options and certainty they deserve.', 68890, 0), (432672, 'Don''t take too much comfort in the fact that you''re successful today because tomorrow could bring failure. There''s no surety in life.', 68891, 0), (432673, 'Health care confronts us with a difficult test. We have never corrected failure in something so deeply embedded in people''s lives and in the economy without the pressure of an outright crisis.', 13590, 0), (432674, 'I believe there''s only one regulation in life that works: failure.', 66963, 0), (432675, 'Success is more difficult to handle than failure.', 4001, 0), (432676, 'The terror of failure can make you feel like a failure. So a bunch of people think you''re not very good at your thing. How much do you invest in what they say? How much do you care? Failure is not putting yourself on the line.', 1479, 0), (432677, 'What strikes me is that there''s a very fine line between success and failure. Just one ingredient can make the difference.', 24279, 0), (432678, 'I don''t think anybody whose ever been divorced can tell you divorce is easy or fun or feels like anything other than a tremendous failure.', 1855, 0), (432679, 'Primarily affecting low-information voters and members of the mainstream media, Obama Worship Syndrome attributes impossible capabilities to Obama''s political opponents, finds excuses for every Obama failure in everyone around him and praises the president as the finest politician - nay, human being - of our time.', 17797, 0), (432680, 'Vietnam was a palpable failure. And of course, in retrospect, it was even more clearly a disaster and a failure than maybe people understood at the time.', 19692, 0), (432681, 'So many times in my life, people have tried to make me a failure.', 68892, 0), (432682, 'Politicians are terrified of losing touch with folks back home but content to be clueless about government''s failure to fix real problems.', 66623, 0), (432683, 'In my memoir, I admit that I''ve been as fearful of success as of failure. In fact, when ''Passages'' was published, I so dreaded bad reviews that I ran away to Italy with a girlfriend and our children to hide out.', 30206, 0), (432684, 'It is important for investors to understand what they do and don''t know. Learn to recognize that you cannot possibly know what is going to happen in the future, and any investment plan that is dependent on accurately forecasting where markets will be next year is doomed to failure.', 68893, 0), (432685, 'Never be afraid of failure. And don''t stop yourself from doing something you want to do because of what others might think. Only you know yourself best.', 68894, 0), (432686, 'One thing I do believe is I''m a believer in the presence of God. I believe that God is close. Whether it''s in joy, pain or personal failure, I believe that God is close. That much I feel in my life.', 68895, 0), (432687, '''The White Woman on the Green Bicycle'' is a love story mapped onto an unfolding political tragedy: that of the failure of the Independence era in Trinidad.', 37082, 0), (432688, 'It''s not about the failure, it''s about learning from the failures. Failure itself cannot be celebrated.', 54622, 0), (432689, 'When we set up our kids for failure, we set up our workforce for failure, and we set up our economy for failure. I can''t emphasize enough the importance, the absolute importance, of education in achieving long-term economic growth.', 66800, 0), (432690, 'When you learn to keep fighting in the face of potential failure, it gives you a larger skill set to do what you want to do in life. It gives you vision. But you can''t acquire it if you''re afraid of keeping score.', 33654, 0), (432691, 'If China stood on an equal basis with other nations, she could compete freely with them in the economic field and be able to hold her own without failure. But as soon as foreign nations use political power as a shield for their economic designs, then China is at a loss how to resist or to compete successfully with them.', 67071, 0), (432692, 'Writing is harder than acting. I enjoy acting for just the brevity with which you can be in the experience of doing it. Writing is kind of more satisfying in that you''re creating a world and doing something that feels bigger, but it''s very time consuming and has a higher threshold for failure.', 68896, 0), (432693, 'The first week in intelligence school, you learn there are only two conditions in life. There is policy success, or there is intel failure. There is no other condition in life.', 68897, 0), (432694, 'The largest single reason for disappointing travel experiences is the failure to plan properly.', 68898, 0), (432695, 'The failure to invest in youth reflects a lack of compassion and a colossal failure of common sense.', 16899, 0), (432696, 'I guess I''m motivated by the fear of failure to some degree and knowing what can happen when you don''t do things the way you need to do them to have success.', 68258, 0), (432697, 'My citizen activism is a direct outgrowth of a classical and fiscally conservative training in economics at Harvard. It is a perspective rooted in one of the most important concepts in economics - the need for government intervention in the presence of a market failure.', 67884, 0), (432698, 'Because of the failure of the federal government to enforce federal law, we now have ''banks too big to fail,'' unregulated Internet monopoly, and the evisceration of a dispersed and independent media.', 68899, 0), (432699, 'The more important argument against grade curves is that they create an atmosphere that''s toxic by pitting students against one another. At best, it creates a hypercompetitive culture, and at worst, it sends students the message that the world is a zero-sum game: Your success means my failure.', 14960, 0), (432700, 'My work ethic came from my parents and my fear of failure. I came from a small, predominantly black school and I didn''t want to let them down.', 68900, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (432701, 'The paradox is that when we model future designs on past successes, we are inviting failure down the line; when we take into account past failures and anticipate potential new ways in which failure can occur, we are more likely to produce successful designs.', 67673, 0), (432702, 'Thoughtless risks are destructive, of course, but perhaps even more wasteful is thoughtless caution which prompts inaction and promotes failure to seize opportunity.', 66604, 0), (432703, 'Sometimes you learn more from failure than you do from success, and in some ways it''s better to have failure at the beginning of your career, or your life.', 68901, 0), (432704, 'Once you can accept failure, you can have fun and success.', 68299, 0), (432705, 'Success needs no explanation. Failure does not have one that matters.', 23411, 0), (432706, 'It''s okay to fail ''cause there''s no failure, you''re just informing the richness of your experience, and that''s - that''s the greatest gift you can possibly give yourself.', 68902, 0), (432707, 'Kids have been let down by adults - we''ve tried to give them too much, we''ve tried not to impose discipline. We''ve tried to make their lives easier and, in doing so, we''ve taken something away from them. Kids like boundaries, they also like to be pushed, need to learn what failure is all about, need guidance.', 68903, 0), (432708, 'We will fiercely challenge those forces within the education establishment who impede innovation in our schools and who protect and defend inequality and institutional failure.', 68904, 0), (432709, 'I''ve achieved everything I''ve wanted to achieve, so I''m not scared of failure. I never gave up, however bad the injuries got.', 68905, 0), (432710, 'Like prospecting in the 19th century, reconnaissance of the asteroids would of necessity take place in an arena where trouble is likely and help is distant. Heroic stories of individual triumph and failure, set on landscapes never seen by humankind, are in the cards.', 13839, 0), (432711, 'I feel that marriage can lead to the ultimate rejection and failure and divorce and things we all fear.', 15814, 0), (432712, 'A man can get discouraged many times but he is not a failure until he begins to blame somebody else and stops trying.', 1069, 0), (432713, 'I''m hopeful. I know there is a lot of ambition in Washington, obviously. But I hope the ambitious realize that they are more likely to succeed with success as opposed to failure.', 2358, 0), (432714, 'I grew up in a household where I learned five things from my old man. You know what they were? You''re no good. You''re a failure. You''re not going to amount to anything. Don''t trust nobody, and don''t tell nobody your business. When I lost to Larry Holmes in 1982, I felt all five of those things smacked me right across the face.', 68906, 0), (432715, 'An investment said to have an 80% chance of success sounds far more attractive than one with a 20% chance of failure. The mind can''t easily recognize that they are the same.', 6017, 0), (432716, 'I''ve accepted that I was a failure in politics. I was not qualified for the job.', 68907, 0), (432717, 'War is tragedy. The great war stories are tragedies. It''s the failure of diplomacy. ''War and Peace,'' ''A Farewell to Arms,'' ''For Whom the Bell Tolls.'' Those are some of the greatest tragedies.', 2221, 0), (432718, 'Lacking the direct test of success or failure, the voter tends to turn, not to those politicians whose measures have the best chance of success, but to those with the ability to ''sell'' their propaganda. Without grasping logical chains of deduction, the average voter will never be able to discover the error that the ruler makes.', 17756, 0), (432719, 'I don''t want success to affect me to that extent that I change or failure to that extent that I get sad, bitter and negative.', 68908, 0), (432720, 'Even people who despise ego and aspire to humility, who plan to be humble once they are successful, are worried that actually enacting those beliefs would sentence them to a life of obscurity or weakness or failure.', 14605, 0), (432721, 'I do public appearances. I''m bluff, hearty, goofy. I wear loud clothes, and I read the funny bits. I occasionally get taken to task for one thing or another, and I acknowledge my fault, my flaw, my failure, and I move on.', 2631, 0), (432722, 'Boys with a ''failure to launch'' are invisible to most girls. With poor social skills, the boys feel anger at their fear of being rejected and self-loathing at their inability to compete.', 18071, 0), (432723, 'What America does best is produce the ability to accept failure.', 2505, 0), (432724, 'We''re very good at talking about the individual in American politics and excellent at talking about the government. But we have little ability to even acknowledge everything that exists in the middle, and given how influential politics is on every other part of our life, I think that failure of discourse is pretty corrosive to our overall culture.', 9371, 0), (432725, 'Every individual suffers from the fear of failure, but you can change your destiny only when you overcome it.', 67717, 0), (432726, 'The dumb-manager theory of business problems just didn''t hold water for me. There had to be a deeper reason why smart people would make decisions that lead to failure.', 14926, 0), (432727, 'My biggest failure is ''Metal Gear.'' It''s my biggest failure and my biggest success.', 68909, 0), (432728, 'The attributes for entrepreneurs cut both ways. You need the ability to ignore inconvenient facts and see the world as it should be and not as it is. This inspires people to take huge leaps of faith. But this blindness to facts can be a liability, too. The characteristics that help entrepreneurs succeed can also lead to their failure.', 34883, 0), (432729, 'Our educational system is not preparing people for the 21st Century. Failure is an essential part of entrepreneurship. If you work hard, you can get an ''A'' pretty much guaranteed, but in entrepreneurship, that''s not how it works.', 34883, 0), (432730, 'Ideology, politics and journalism, which luxuriate in failure, are impotent in the face of hope and joy.', 10731, 0), (432731, 'The idea of capitalism is not just success but also the failure that allows success to happen.', 10731, 0), (432732, 'Adam Smith''s huge failure was the fact that he did not foresee the industrial revolution.', 10731, 0), (432733, 'The Communist bloc of old was a study in the failure of failure. Losers in the Soviet economy were the people at the end of the long lines for consumer goods. Worse losers were the people who had spent hours getting to the head of the line, only to be told that the goods were unavailable.', 10731, 0), (432734, 'So while I will never minimize the costs involved in military action, I am convinced that a failure to act in Libya would have carried a far greater price for America.', 1693, 0), (432735, 'The Bush Administration''s failure to be consistently involved in helping Israel achieve peace with the Palestinians has been both wrong for our friendship with Israel, as well as badly damaging to our standing in the Arab world.', 1693, 0), (432736, 'In America, there''s a failure to appreciate Europe''s leading role in the world.', 1693, 0), (432737, 'President Obama''s astonishing failure to secure an orderly transition in Iraq has unnecessarily put at risk the victories that were won through the blood and sacrifice of thousands of American men and women.', 52321, 0), (432738, 'We will all fail in life, but nobody has to be a failure. Failing at a thing doesn''t make you a failure. You are only a failure when you quit trying.', 1206, 0), (432739, 'When I was young, I observed that nine out of ten things I did were failures. So I did ten times more work.', 266, 0), (432740, 'My reputation grows with every failure.', 266, 0), (432741, 'It''s impossible for a Democrat to be a failure. It''s impossible for a Democrat to be a reprobate. It''s impossible for a Democrat to be a mess. It just isn''t possible, as far as the mind-set of the media is concerned.', 17531, 0), (432742, 'In the 1940s, traveling for an African was a complicated process. All Africans over the age of sixteen were compelled to carry ''Native passes'' issued by the Native Affairs Department and were required to show that pass to any white policeman, civil servant, or employer. Failure to do so could mean arrest, trial, a jail sentence or fine.', 1722, 0), (432743, 'If my child had prejudice in his head, I''d be ashamed. I would see it as my failure as a parent.', 2065, 0), (432744, 'Big companies are like marching bands. Even if half the band is playing random notes, it still sounds kind of like music. The concealment of failure is built into them.', 1002, 0), (432745, 'Sometimes failure isn''t an opportunity in disguise, it''s just you.', 1002, 0), (432746, 'The thing I always say to people is this: ''If you avoid failure, you also avoid success.''', 66592, 0), (432747, 'I like the possibility of failure. I don''t want to be in a comfortable zone.', 60783, 0), (432748, 'The failure to set standards for Palestinian conduct hurts the cause of peace.', 67439, 0), (432749, 'In Arab capitals, the failure of the United States to stop Iran''s nuclear program is understood as American weakness in the struggle for dominance in the Middle East, making additional cooperation from Arab leaders on Israeli-Palestinian issues even less likely.', 67439, 0), (432750, 'I read less and less. I have not forgiven books for their failure to tell me the truth and make me happy.', 12469, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (432751, 'Pride is ugly. It says, ''If you succeed, I am a failure.''', 1826, 0), (432752, 'Bacon is so good by itself that to put it in any other food is an admission of failure. You''re basically saying, ''I can''t make this other food taste good, so I''ll throw in bacon.''', 9137, 0), (432753, 'A joke is a way to say, ''I''m going to do something funny now. If I don''t get a laugh at the end, I''m a failure.''', 9137, 0), (432754, 'I think that a failure of statistical thinking is the major intellectual shortcoming of our universities, journalism and intellectual culture.', 3432, 0), (432755, 'Given the extent of the exposures of major banks around the world to A.I.G., and in light of the extreme fragility of the system, there was a significant risk that A.I.G.''s failure could have sparked a global banking panic.', 66590, 0), (432756, 'In the future, financial firms of any type whose failure would pose a systemic risk must accept especially close regulatory scrutiny of their risk-taking.', 66590, 0), (432757, 'The failure of Lehman Brothers demonstrated that liquidity provision by the Federal Reserve would not be sufficient to stop the crisis substantial fiscal resources were necessary. ', 66590, 0), (432758, 'I even get inspired by movies that aren''t very good, because there''s always something good in movies that are collectively thought of as a failure. There''s good in everything, I find.', 5194, 0), (432759, 'The most irresistible charm of youth is its bubbling enthusiasm. Youth sees no darkness ahead - no defile that has no outlet - it forgets that there is such a thing as failure in the world and believes that mankind has been waiting all these centuries for him to come and be the liberator of truth and energy and beauty.', 4025, 0), (432760, 'There''s a difference between a failure and a fiasco... a fiasco is a disaster of mythic proportions.', 68239, 0), (432761, 'Failure is simply the non-presence of success. But a fiasco is a disaster of mythic proportions.', 68239, 0), (432762, 'If anyone has seen success and failure on a global stage, it''s my friend Steve Forbes.', 66565, 0), (432763, 'I love Rauschenberg. I love that he created a turning point in visual history, that he redefined the idea of beauty, that he combined painting, sculpture, photography, and everyday life with such gall, and that he was interested in, as he put it, ''the ability to conceive failure as progress.''', 19958, 0), (432764, 'It would be great to be able to pass on to someone all of the successes, the failures, and the knowledge that one has had. To help someone, avoid all the fire, pain and anxiety would be wonderful.', 35699, 0), (432765, 'I have a lack of fear, whereas in the past the fear of failure was a powerful motivator. Anyway, I have great expectations for the future, but I just don''t know if I''m the monarch of all I survey.', 35699, 0), (432766, 'I think that big, sort of theatrical relaunches tend to set you up for failure and hype.', 18085, 0), (432767, 'If we can actually decrease the failure rate from nine out of 10 drugs failing in clinical trials and instead have seven out of 10 instead failing, that is a major victory for drug discovery and for people having better therapy.', 68910, 0), (432768, 'Katie Price is no exception. She, too, is - in a distinctive way - a philosopher. Partially, Katie Price''s philosophy is one of extraordinary confidence. She is remarkable not for her looks or antics but because of her tremendous self-assurance and her unwillingness to be intimidated by criticism or failure.', 639, 0), (432769, 'A street full of electric light is a sign of civic failure and is an insulting injury to the soul. Shutting out the night is as disastrous as shutting out the light.', 10407, 0), (432770, 'I realized that I was afraid to really, really try something, 100%, because I had never reached true failure.', 60178, 0), (432771, 'When people have a willpower failure, it''s because they haven''t anticipated a situation that''s going to come along.', 11321, 0), (432772, 'Modesty means admitting the possibility of error, subsuming the self for the good of the whole, remaining open to surprise and the gifts that only failure can bring. There are many ways to practice it. Try taking up golf. Or making your own bagels. Or raising a teenager.', 36805, 0), (432773, 'We have to provide more visibility, more certainty to the investors and reduce the cost of failure.', 68911, 0), (432774, 'For me, utter failure is to make a film that people pay their money to go see and they don''t like.', 3497, 0), (432775, 'I think my whole life, because of where I came from, I had a fear of failure.', 19506, 0), (432776, 'There are many victories worse than a defeat.', 215, 0), (432777, 'The only failure one should fear, is not hugging to the purpose they see as best.', 215, 0), (432778, 'I always write about subjects which attract me because if I didn''t, it would be awful, a failure.', 1426, 0), (432779, 'Historically, defense spending cuts have preceded increased international turmoil as America''s global enemies sense a failure of will.', 17797, 0), (432780, 'Failure is simply a few errors in judgment, repeated every day.', 1295, 0), (432781, 'My biggest fear is doing the same things 10 years from now. That would be a failure. It''s something you have to constantly reassess, and asking yourself what you are going to do next makes it a good, long full journey.', 7961, 0), (432782, 'No one ought to be under any illusion that Cheney privately thinks himself a failure.', 68912, 0), (432783, 'First developed as a weapon by the U.S. Army, VX is an oily, odorless and tasteless liquid that kills on contact with the skin or when inhaled in aerosol form. Like other nerve agents, it is treatable in the first minutes after exposure but otherwise leads swiftly to fatal convulsions and respiratory failure.', 68912, 0), (432784, 'I''m drawn to failure. I feel like I''m contending with it constantly in my own life.', 852, 0), (432785, 'I was raised in the ''70s, and I''ve worked with people I love, and I''ve been on sets with my parents, with people who run a set and require of actors a sense of liberty and freedom and exploration and failure into brave achievement.', 68913, 0), (432786, 'A failure to act is a terrible, stunning legacy for any leader. But far worse when it is the president of the United States. And that''s the point driven home by Romney''s selection of Ryan, who dared to lead when Obama did not.', 67775, 0), (432787, 'I have tried every diet to lose weight. When you restrict yourself, you''re setting yourself up for failure.', 67336, 0), (432788, 'Capitalism, after all, is no fun when real failure becomes a possibility.', 11156, 0), (432789, 'Solyndra''s failure isn''t a reason for the government to give up on alternative energy, any more than the failure of Pets.com during the Internet bubble means that venture capital should steer clear of tech projects.', 11156, 0), (432790, 'I was always told that music isn''t a ''realistic'' path to take, and like a normal human being, I doubted myself over and over because I was afraid of failure.', 68914, 0), (432791, 'In reality, I am more a professor, one who reflects and mediates on spiritual questions. Practical governance is not my strong point, and this is certainly a weakness. But I do not see myself as a failure. For eight years, I carried out my work.', 856, 0), (432792, 'As long as there are people in education making excuses for failure, cursing future generations with a culture of low expectations, denying children access to the best that has been thought and written, because Nemo and the Mister Men are more relevant, the battle needs to be joined.', 68003, 0), (432793, 'Low standards are a tactic that takes pressure off teachers'' unions by accepting mediocrity and failure for kids.', 68245, 0), (432794, 'I''ve had a lot of disappointments. I think my biggest disappointment is the failure of elected officials to make good on their promises in regards to the environment or anything else, really. I have very little faith in politicians.', 21274, 0), (432795, 'Every time I act on a fear, I feel disappointed in myself. I have a lot of fear. If I can quit all fear in my life and all guilt, then I tend to be much, much more living up to my standards. I''ve never seen a person fail if they didn''t fear failure.', 66947, 0), (432796, 'The very reasons sometimes that you make a film are the reasons for its failure.', 68229, 0), (432797, 'I''m bound to fail when I write in Italian, but unlike my sense of failure in the past, this doesn''t torment or grieve me.', 1590, 0), (432798, 'People never confess to failure. They should.', 67778, 0), (432799, 'The failure to readily identify the battle between good and evil is a nagging, ongoing, dangerous pattern that shows no sign of easing up any time soon.', 68915, 0), (432800, 'Increasing extremism - across Africa and the world - must be understood in the context of the failure of our leaders properly to manage diversity within their borders.', 67778, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (432801, 'Within the U.S., the Obama presidency will be mainly measured by the success or failure of his economic policies. And here, I fear, the monstrous stimulus package with which this administration stumbled out of the gate will prove to be Obama''s Waterloo.', 1920, 0), (432802, 'With everything that is complex, we learn. If you don''t learn, then it''s an utter and abject failure. If you do learn, and you''re able to apply that to the next situation, then you take away a measure of success.', 1793, 0), (432803, 'We have actually experienced in recent months a dramatic demonstration of an unprecedented intelligence failure, perhaps the most significant intelligence failure in the history of the United States.', 17524, 0), (432804, 'In Iraq we must succeed. Failure is not an option.', 17524, 0), (432805, 'Like Lyndon Johnson, President Obama understands that timidity in a time of troubles is a prescription for failure.', 19692, 0), (432806, 'The consequence of the Bay of Pigs failure wasn''t an acceptance of Castro and his control of Cuba but, rather, a renewed determination to bring him down by stealth.', 19692, 0), (432807, 'Failure''s a natural part of life.', 18212, 0), (432808, 'I love when me and my friends don''t know how to make something - there''s that risk of failure, which should be there. If it''s guaranteed not to fail, it''s something you already know how to do.', 25425, 0), (432809, 'There were times in ''Adaptation'' during the editing where I really thought, ''Okay, well, this was a noble failure. I tried to do something good, but this is not going to work.''', 25425, 0), (432810, 'Already from your own cells scientists can grow skin, cartilage, noses, blood vessels, bladders and windpipes. In the future, scientists will grow more complex organs, like livers and kidneys. The phrase ''organ failure'' will disappear.', 1821, 0), (432811, 'Sometimes we never see what failure is and often fail to recognize it.', 66796, 0), (432812, 'How important is failure - yes, failure - to the health of a thriving, innovative business? So important that Ratan Tata, chairman of India''s largest corporation, gives an annual award to the employee who comes up with the best idea that failed.', 66796, 0), (432813, 'In my view, the first requirement for success for an entrepreneur is to dream big. The second aspect that prevents entrepreneurs from succeeding is fear of failure.', 66796, 0), (432814, 'When you experience a failure as a leader, don''t hide it - talk about it. Your missed opportunity will encourage others to take risks.', 66796, 0), (432815, 'Call it the Tiger Mom effect: In the business world today, failure is apparently not an option.', 66796, 0), (432816, 'The enemy of human happiness as well as the cause of poverty and starvation is not the birth of children. It is the failure of people to do with the earth what God could teach them to do if only they would ask and then obey, for they are agents unto themselves.', 9158, 0), (432817, 'The very phrase ''Oscar night'' used to accelerate my pulse. For one thing - dating myself - it meant Bob Hope. He always had good, strong jokes, that faultless delivery, and always a new joke about his own films'' failure - once again - to be honored.', 12902, 0), (432818, 'You just don''t go out when you''re over 55 years of age, have a colossal failure, and expect to find work in your field again.', 66696, 0), (432819, 'There is no question that the Islamic State will be defeated in Mosul the real question is what comes afterward. Can the post-Islamic State effort resolve the squabbling likely to arise over numerous issues and bring lasting stability to one of Iraq''s most diverse and challenging provinces? Failure to do so could lead to ISIS 3.0. ', 68916, 0), (432820, 'Iraq''s Sunnis need to be brought back into the fold. They need to feel as though they have a stake in the success of Iraq rather than a stake in its failure.', 68916, 0), (432821, 'It is often the failure who is the pioneer in new lands, new undertakings, and new forms of expression.', 2567, 0), (432822, 'A failure is a man who has blundered, but is not able to cash in the experience.', 4, 0), (432823, 'This is true enough, but success is the next best thing to happiness, and if you can''t be happy as a success, it''s very unlikely that you would find a deeper, truer happiness in failure.', 14083, 0), (432824, 'The freedom to fail is vital if you''re going to succeed. Most successful people fail from time to time, and it is a measure of their strength that failure merely propels them into some new attempt at success.', 14083, 0), (432825, 'The federal government has been a proven failure in picking winners and losers in the energy sector.', 68917, 0), (432826, 'If terrorists are already on our southern border, a national-security failure has already occurred.', 68917, 0), (432827, 'Some parents believe that competition helps prepare children to succeed. Others fear that their children will not be able to handle failure.', 57649, 0), (432828, 'Federal regulations forbid delaying inspections for fracture-critical bridges like the fallen Minneapolis bridge - the kind with a lack of redundancy in design, so that a single failure in a load-bearing part can cause the entire bridge to collapse.', 57649, 0), (432829, 'Not many people are really that meticulous with what they do, I suppose, but I''m just a control freak and terribly afraid of failure or regret. I work very hard on these things.', 22745, 0), (432830, 'The failure of world leaders to act on the critical issue of global warming is often blamed on economic considerations.', 13824, 0), (432831, 'Brain surgeons are dealing with the very last thread of life, and they have to be very confident, but I think they tend to remember their failures rather than their successes, and that must be very hard. Who do you share that failure with? That''s why their personal lives are often disastrous.', 68918, 0), (432832, 'My father was not a failure. After all, he was the father of a president of the United States.', 16121, 0), (432833, 'We know there is no such thing as freedom without the risk of failure.', 67560, 0), (432834, 'Try not to say, ''I''m a failure.'' Instead, ask, ''What can I do better? What did I do wrong?'' Then re-approach.', 1860, 0), (432835, 'Whenever you have a failure or setback, you need to take a step back and find out what you can learn from the scenario. What did you do to contribute to that failure? This way, you can make sure you don''t repeat that pattern.', 1860, 0), (432836, 'I think that the failure of newspaper competition in a community is a very serious handicap to the dissemination of the knowledge that the citizens need to participate in a democracy.', 9501, 0), (432837, 'The democratic system is challenged by the failure in television because our evening news programmes have gone for an attempt to entertain as much as to inform in the desperate fight for ratings.', 9501, 0), (432838, 'The British health care system is a blueprint for the failure of Obamacare, as it is structured.', 38698, 0), (432839, 'Basically, I still have the privacy that all celebrities crave, except for those celebrities who feel that privacy reflects some kind of failure on their part.', 61610, 0), (432840, 'The only TV I would be interested in exploring would be live television. There''s no substitute for a team of artists performing at their peak live when failure is possible. It''s a high-wire act. That excites me.', 28610, 0), (432841, 'The only reason my work seems to be eclectic up to a certain period is because I was a failure as an actor.', 66237, 0), (432842, 'When preaching is done right, it can change lives. When it''s done badly, my failure goes beyond the merely human.', 4328, 0), (432843, 'All actors should experience public failure.', 68919, 0), (432844, 'Failure to take note of the fact that the character of twentieth-century humanity differs from that of humanity in the fifteenth century, let alone before and at the time of the Mystery of Golgotha, is to sleep through the process of world evolution.', 14254, 0), (432845, 'The young think that failure is the Siberian end of the line, banishment from all the living, and tend to do what I then did - which was to hide.', 67562, 0), (432846, 'E! has just become a sad, sad place to live. They don''t know what they''re doing; they have no ideas... everything they do just is a failure.', 2202, 0), (432847, 'The Bay of Pigs became a metaphor for feckless folly and failure.', 54786, 0), (432848, 'There has been a failure to grasp how competing narratives fight for the attention of angry young Muslims, and we have grossly underestimated the appeal of the jihadist brand.', 10487, 0), (432849, 'People think when you have a, quote, ''bank failure,'' that that is the end of the bank. And it isn''t necessarily.', 66573, 0), (432850, 'Yes, ''Aagadu'' was a failure. I was dejected for a couple of months, since there was a lot at stake.', 68920, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (432851, 'The publishing scene in India is evolving rapidly, and the key challenge is to keep reinventing oneself so that one does not become formulaic. Sometimes it is safer to deal with the consequences of failure than the fruits of success. Remaining on one''s toes is critical, and often one finds that success makes one complacent.', 22495, 0), (432852, 'Since so many romantic comedies vary little in their storyline, the success or failure of such movies depends largely on whether we believe in the relationship of the protagonists.', 67020, 0), (432853, 'I''m scared of failure so much more than any of the other girls I compete against that I work so much harder than they possibly could. I''m totally down with spiders and frogs and heights and snakes - everything I''m cool with it. ', 25405, 0), (432854, 'I''ve learned to think in terms of having a long career. Actors can have very long careers that last until the day we die, but there will be moments when you''ll feel like you''re a failure or when you''re disappointed in yourself.', 68921, 0), (432855, 'My friend was on dialysis for six years before he got a new kidney. I was on dialysis for eight months. I''m almost not even the typical person who has kidney failure.', 68922, 0), (432856, 'I was pretty bad. When I first was diagnosed with kidney failure, my function - the function of my kidney was less than 8 percent.', 68922, 0), (432857, 'I already had high blood pressure. I have hypertension. And I think the chemo was just too much for my kidneys. And they went into failure. And that was September 12th of 2008. And the doctor rushed me right to the hospital.', 68922, 0), (432858, 'George W. Bush is history''s president, a man for whom the long-term success or failure of democracy in Iraq will determine his place in history.', 17895, 0), (432859, 'Once our country is fully engulfed in a debt crisis, our economy will be torn apart, and every American will be a victim of the federal government''s failure to prevent this disaster.', 68923, 0), (432860, 'Wherever there''s an all-encompassing ''always,'' ''all'' or ''never'' in your life, it''s a sign that your mischievous subconscious is setting you up for failure by consistently leading you back toward these repeat performances.', 5238, 0), (432861, 'Failure is your invention.', 5789, 0), (432862, 'If your startup is only in the development or idea stage, there is almost no better predictor of failure - I mean, utter failure, scorched-earth bankruptcy - than raising too much money in the first round.', 68924, 0), (432863, 'Failure is an amazing data point that tells you which direction not to go.', 68925, 0), (432864, 'Every large brand has franchisees and stores that don''t make it. It''s unfortunate, and Cold Stone did everything it could to support its franchisees, but some failure rate is part of the business.', 67855, 0), (432865, 'If those committed to the quest fail, they will be forgiven. When lost, they will find another way. The moral imperative of humanism is the endeavor alone, whether successful or not, provided the effort is honorable and failure memorable.', 44747, 0), (432866, 'My failures may be my greatest successes. It is in failure that I have often drawn closer to God, learn to depend more on Him than myself, gained self-knowledge, and seen things in their right perspective.', 9130, 0), (432867, 'Divorce is so common and accepted in America that beating myself up over it may sound ridiculous. But I was raised to believe that divorce wasn''t an option; to me, divorce equaled failure. I wasn''t able to change that equation until I found myself in the right relationship.', 56, 0), (432868, 'I don''t lose any sleep at night over the potential for failure. I cannot even spell the word.', 38429, 0), (432869, 'While entrepreneurs spend a lot of effort trying to avoid failure, sometimes the lessons one learns from those missteps can be invaluable.', 66659, 0), (432870, 'The album ''Cheers to the Fall'' is really kind of me breaking out and being like, ''Listen, I don''t care about criticism, and I don''t care about possibility of failure. I''m going to do it. And if I do fail, well then, here''s to it.''', 68926, 0), (432871, 'When my father left us, my mother went back to school immediately. She went to school in the day while we were at school, and she worked at night. She worked very hard to never let someone define her as a victim or a failure.', 66657, 0), (432872, 'If your current get-rich project fails, take what you learned and try something else. Keep repeating until something lucky happens. The universe has plenty of luck to go around; you just need to keep your hand raised until it''s your turn. It helps to see failure as a road and not a wall.', 101, 0), (432873, 'I wouldn''t call Loopt a failure. It didn''t turn out like I wanted, for sure, but it was fun, I learned a lot, and I made enough money to start investing, which led me to my current job. I don''t regret it at all.', 68927, 0), (432874, 'Failure will happen. It''s a normal part of the startup process.', 68928, 0), (432875, 'While ''The Owner''s Manual'' is not a formula for guaranteed success by any means, we''re confident it will help reduce the failure rate of most startups that use our Customer Development process.', 68928, 0), (432876, 'In corporations, the penalty for repeated failure on known tasks is being reassigned to other tasks or asked to leave the company.', 68928, 0), (432877, 'While the public school rewards failure by throwing more government money at failing school systems, the voucher system does the opposite.', 19591, 0), (432878, 'Every entrepreneur knows how agonizingly difficult it is to make the decision to give it your all, knowing that failure is inevitable; the successful ones know that the only way to get back up is through learning from that failure.', 19591, 0), (432879, 'There are a whole host of psychological phenomenon humans have developed to protect ourselves from the sting of failure, from holding ourselves less accountable for our failures than we do other people, to letting our fear paralyze us and keep us from even trying.', 19591, 0), (432880, 'It is incredibly important to set goals for your business, as if you have no direction for your business, your online business will be a failure.', 19591, 0), (432881, 'I grew and learned, journeyed and understood, that someone who is afraid of failing won''t get anywhere, and someone who dares to do it runs the risk of failure if they don''t learn, correct their mistakes, and get back up.', 19591, 0), (432882, 'It''s only a risk if you think there''s a chance of failure.', 67035, 0), (432883, 'The offshoring of American jobs by global corporations and the deregulation of the U.S. financial system have resulted in American economic failure.', 68899, 0), (432884, 'I mean, I love L.A. - I love living here. But I wish that we could make things without the need to hit a home run every single time. It''s a unique thing to Hollywood that if you don''t do that every time, then you''re considered a failure. But it''s like, ''Well, are you making movies to be successful? Or are you making movies to learn something?''', 55840, 0), (432885, 'I was in kidney failure. I ended up having a kidney transplant on my 21st birthday.', 68264, 0), (432886, 'Ego is certainly there in many of the greatest and most dizzying tales of success - but it''s there in some of the greatest stories of failure and self-implosion as well.', 14605, 0), (432887, 'I don''t think one should attribute the success and failure of a film to a single actor. When you decide to do a film, you weigh the pros and cons before taking a call. Only when you run out of patience, get insecure, and feel your career is heading nowhere do you sign anything that comes your way.', 68929, 0), (432888, 'I don''t take it very seriously. You shouldn''t let your success get to your head or failure get to your heart. This is most commonly said. But people don''t really practise it. I don''t see myself as a celebrity it has not sunk in. I just see myself as someone doing a nine-to-six job like a techie. ', 68929, 0), (432889, 'There is failure in every industry there is failure in every step. It''s just that we are working in an industry where everything is just out there that is why it looks so magnified. But failure is a part of life. ', 67036, 0), (432890, 'My feeling, based on my own experience, is that aiming for grandiosity is the fastest route to failure.', 20595, 0), (432891, 'I feel, in the end, as if everything I''ve done has been a failure.', 11500, 0), (432892, 'By far the most important factor in the success or failure of any school, far more important than tests or standards or business-model methods of accountability, is simply attracting the best-educated, most exciting young people into urban schools and keeping them there.', 11500, 0), (432893, 'A fictionalised memoir of my father would be a failure as a novel.', 9692, 0), (432894, 'While it''s important to accept failure and not let it bog you down, it''s also perfectly acceptable to get upset about it as long as you remember that failure is a stepping stone in your journey that is getting you to where you need to be.', 53857, 0), (432895, 'We''ve all experienced those days when we feel like an absolute failure. It''s a normal feeling when things don''t go as exactly planned. And, when we feel like that, it''s challenging to think of yourself as a successful individual.', 53857, 0), (432896, 'We decided to try in vitro, because both Peter and I felt we couldn''t handle another failure. When I miscarried after that, we had to come to terms with the possibility that this wasn''t meant to be.', 63466, 0), (432897, 'The greatest challenge to most innovation centers around the world is many nations'' punitive attitudes towards failure. In most of the world, if your first business fails, no one will work with you again. But, trial and error is the genesis of innovation.', 29731, 0), (432898, 'Success and failure are equally surprising.', 68394, 0), (432899, 'The Tea Party people say they''re angry about socialism, but maybe they''re really angry about capitalism. If there''s a sense of being looked down upon, it''s that sense of failure that''s built into a system that assures everyone they can make it to the top, but then reserves the top for only a tiny fraction of the strivers.', 19519, 0), (432900, 'The failure to work out sensible budgets makes it impossible for government agencies to make long-term plans, and instead leaves them scrambling to spend money in the short term.', 2829, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (432901, 'I felt like a failure for so long because I wasn''t able to access myself in the way I knew I would have if I was going to make music that mattered. I knew I was going to have to learn how to be honest.', 67046, 0), (432902, 'The failure of one regional bank, assuming it is following a traditional model, will not threaten the entire system.', 68930, 0), (432903, 'I think there is a failure in foreign policy. And you have to acknowledge that under Barack Obama, Hillary Clinton was the architect of that foreign policy. Whether it was malevolent or not, I don''t know.', 68931, 0), (432904, 'Movies are not novels, and that''s why, when filmmakers try to adapt novels, particularly long or complex novels, the result is almost always failure. It can''t be done.', 496, 0), (432905, 'There''s no question that Kennedy was an utter failure as a passer of laws during his proverbial thousand days.', 11762, 0), (432906, 'I wanted to give an honest insight into a consuming Tour. It''s turned out pretty interesting because there aren''t many books out there documenting someone''s failure.', 66926, 0), (432907, 'I''ve had my share of struggle. I believe, never take success to your head or failure to your heart.', 68932, 0), (432908, 'I didn''t allow failure to break my heart. So I wouldn''t allow success to bloat my head.', 68932, 0), (432909, 'I didn''t fear failure. I expected failure.', 1039, 0), (432910, 'I think I''ve always been somebody, since the deaths of my father and brother, who was afraid to hope. So, I was more prepared for failure and for rejection than for success.', 1039, 0), (432911, 'If it''s a good work of adaptation, the book should remain a book and the film should remain a film, and you should not necessarily read the book to see the film. If you do need that, then that means that it''s a failure. That is what I think.', 2030, 0), (432912, 'I''ve loved every minute I''ve spent in television. And I''ve had much more failure, as traditionally measured, than success in television. I''ve done four shows, and only one of them was the ''West Wing.''', 1482, 0), (432913, 'Failure to curb temperature increases will impact all countries, Ireland included, but with the most immediate and drastic effects being felt, in many instances, by the most vulnerable countries and communities.', 68933, 0), (432914, 'I like Diaspora because it''s audacious, it''s driven by passion, and it''s very, very hard to do. After all, who in their right mind would set as a goal taking on Facebook? That''s sort of like deciding to build a better search engine - very expensive, with a high likelihood of failure.', 67495, 0), (432915, 'The failure of the White House and Congress to seriously address the nation''s fiscal situation is certain to broaden the belief among many voters that the U.S. political system is broken.', 27482, 0), (432916, 'Lincoln made mistakes. Roosevelt made mistakes. Eisenhower made mistakes. The Battle of the Bulge was the biggest intelligence failure in American military history, much bigger than any in Vietnam or now. We didn''t know that the Soviets were moving 400,000 or 500,000 troops. We missed it.', 67368, 0), (432917, 'My greatest sense of accomplishment has come from having two amazing sons, but it''s also a paradox in that the times when I felt like the biggest failure have been times when I felt like, as a parent, I wasn''t making the right decisions or succeeding in the way that I should.', 21674, 0), (432918, 'Well, I think it''s too early to call Fallujah a failure.', 67564, 0), (432919, 'Former Sen. Alan Simpson of Wyoming, the co-author of the 1986 Simpson-Mazzoli immigration reform bill, has said the failure of that bill was a function of the lack of an ID card system.', 68934, 0), (432920, 'It''s a strange failure of the literary world that Updike never quite received his due. Despite winning two Pulitzers and two National Book Awards and countless other awards and honours, he was denied the Nobel.', 30978, 0), (432921, 'If we don''t succeed, we run the risk of failure.', 13473, 0), (432922, 'I teach students that what people say about failure in politics is mostly wrong. People always told me, ''They''ll praise you on your way up and kick you on your way down.'' That wasn''t my experience. I can''t walk down the street in Toronto without someone coming up and saying hello.', 16292, 0), (432923, 'In 1999, I was in St. Louis with Martin Luther King III as we led protests against the state''s failure to hire minority contractors for highway construction projects. We went at dawn on a summer day with over a thousand people and performed acts of civil disobedience.', 68935, 0), (432924, 'I like to do matrices. One option per line, different facets for each column. Salary, location, happiness index, failure index, and all that.', 68936, 0), (432925, 'Coming to terms with the fact that my marriage was a failure was devastating and very difficult.', 2046, 0), (432926, 'Coming to terms with the fact that my marriage was a failure was devastating and very difficult. I blamed myself for a lot of things. It took me a very long time to get over it.', 2046, 0), (432927, 'If you get into a Broadway show and it doesn''t work, you''re a failure. And if it does work, you may be stuck for who knows how long. It just doesn''t sound great to me!', 1377, 0), (432928, 'If you''ve gone into a marriage and you haven''t been clear about how you''re going to handle money, how you want to raise kids, who is going to work or stay home or what have you, then you''ve set yourself up for failure.', 68937, 0), (432929, 'The historic lesson is that it was a strategic failure to go into Iraq. History will not be and should not be kind with that decision.', 68938, 0), (432930, 'I can plunk out enough chords to write a song, but I''m completely afraid to play guitar in front of other people. It''s a fear of failure, I guess.', 67484, 0), (432931, 'Overhead will eat you alive if not constantly viewed as a parasite to be exterminated. Never mind the bleating of those you employ. Hold out until mutiny is imminent before employing even a single additional member of staff. More startups are wrecked by overstaffing than by any other cause, bar failure to monitor cash flow.', 67811, 0), (432932, 'I lived with this tremendous fear of failure because my father was a playwright and a director, and I think he did a couple of things as a child as an actor as well, and he... he failed, basically.', 14215, 0), (432933, 'My failure to lay aside the sin that so easily entangles is the direct result of my refusal to die to my natural proclivity toward attaining my own freedom, meaning, value, worth, and righteousness - not believing that, by virtue of my Spirit - wrought union with Christ, everything I need, I already possess.', 16728, 0), (432934, 'What is indisputable is the fact that unbelief is the force that gives birth to all of our bad behavior and every moral failure. It is the root.', 16728, 0), (432935, 'You can''t be afraid of the problem. Don''t be afraid of failure; don''t be afraid to make mistakes. Make sure you learn from each step; iterate, and stay as efficient as possible without being paralyzed by a difficult situation.', 68278, 0), (432936, 'George Orwell''s science-fiction classic ''Nineteen Eighty-Four'' wasn''t a failure because the future it predicted failed to come to pass. Rather, it was a resounding success because it helped us prevent that future.', 13423, 0), (432937, 'Sometimes people call me a success for all the reasons that make me think I''m a failure.', 67061, 0), (432938, 'I failed first grade, which is my biggest problem. You always feel like a failure, like you''re stupid.', 274, 0), (432939, 'I may be a successful football player, but I feel like such a failure.', 68939, 0), (432940, 'It''s probably foolish to expect relationships to go on forever and to say that because something only lasts 10 years, it''s a failure.', 68940, 0), (432941, 'Life is nothing but a bunch of experiences. There''s no such thing as success or failure.', 68894, 0), (432942, 'I don''t fear pain or failure anymore because I''m too grateful for the pains and failures of my past - they have made me who I am, and most of the good things in my life are a direct result of them in some way.', 68941, 0), (432943, 'When people read ''Breitbart'' every single day and convince themselves that Barack Obama is a foreign terrorist, that is not a problem of government. That is a problem of community failure, and we have to recognize that.', 9371, 0), (432944, 'Trump''s biggest failure as a political leader is that he sees the worst in people, and he encourages the worst in people.', 9371, 0), (432945, 'In Chicago, you have an absence of strong family units, and that absence gets filled by gangs. You have a failure in the school system, after-school programs and other social programs to help keep kids off the streets. Amnesty International speaks to that in some way, by keeping these issues in the forefront.', 68942, 0), (432946, 'There''s no right or wrong, success or failure.', 682, 0), (432947, 'As long as the G.O.P., led by its increasingly visible women, continues to insist that the problem is not their policies but women''s failure to understand their own lives and interests, the gender gap won''t go away.', 68451, 0), (432948, 'It''s failure, really, that you grow by, although nobody likes to experience it.', 68943, 0), (432949, 'I''m kind of a failure. I mean, I''ll be honest. I''m successful in that I''m getting to work on great stuff, but I think I''m a failure in all the personal stuff that is most important to me.', 17478, 0), (432950, 'So nevertheless, what I''m saying is that what one is - one''s parameters are constantly narrowed by one''s success, and my desire is to widen my field even if I risk failure.', 68090, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (432951, 'I constantly experience failure in that my work is never as good as I want it to be. So I live with failure.', 68090, 0), (432952, 'I see people around me with very unhappy love lives, who may have held out for that perfect somebody. And the failure to achieve that brings along a lot of bitterness which is very unattractive; therefore they''re probably less likely to achieve it.', 5946, 0), (432953, 'Forget about the consequences of failure. Failure is only a temporary change in direction to set you straight for your next success.', 1391, 0), (432954, 'All human actions are equivalent... and all are on principle doomed to failure.', 1301, 0), (432955, 'I think, if you''re in the United States, we''ve seen people trying to speak out in different ways and trying to make themselves heard about the United States'' failure to move on generationally, given the long-festering wound of our history around race.', 68282, 0), (432956, 'Failure is enriching. It''s also important to accept that you''ll make mistakes - it''s how you build your expertise. The trick is to learn a positive lesson from all of life''s negative moments.', 67872, 0), (432957, 'Among all the tests President Obama faced in his first term, his biggest failure was climate change.', 68944, 0), (432958, 'I don''t see divorce as a failure. I see it as the end to a story. In a story, everything has an end and a beginning.', 68945, 0), (432959, 'If you have a level of expectation in your life that you have to be a quote-unquote star, whatever that means, you might be setting yourself up for failure.', 33509, 0), (432960, 'Different parts of the world have different attitudes to failure. Arguably, it may take more courage to be an entrepreneur in Sydney, or Paris, or London, or Japan, or Singapore... but an entrepreneur sees the world for what it could be, not what it is.', 5456, 0), (432961, 'No one suggested Lehman deserved to be saved. But the argument has been made that the crisis might have been less severe if it had been saved, because Lehman''s failure created remarkable uncertainty in the market as investors became confused about the role of the government and whether it was picking winners and losers.', 17666, 0), (432962, 'In truth, in the fairy-tale version of bailing out Lehman, the next domino, A.I.G., would have fallen even harder. If the politics of bailing out Lehman were bad, the politics of bailing out A.I.G. would have been worse. And the systemic risk that a failure of A.I.G. posed was orders of magnitude greater than Lehman''s collapse.', 17666, 0), (432963, 'The failure of Lehman may have allowed the government to do more to prop up the economy than it otherwise could.', 17666, 0), (432964, 'I think, with Hank Paulson, the concept of a bailout was anathema to him from day one. He was a Republican; he''s a free marketeer. He believes in capitalism, and part of capitalism is believing in failure. And so the idea of bailing out an institution, I think, went against every part of him.', 17666, 0), (432965, 'I think to visualize failure as you''re starting off is really a bad thing to do.', 68946, 0), (432966, 'When I started running cross-country and track in high school, literally every race was a failure.', 68947, 0), (432967, 'Running helped me learn how to deal with failure, and failure is a big part of the Internet business.', 68947, 0), (432968, 'Anybody who dies with money in the bank is a failure.', 68948, 0), (432969, 'Greatly begin. Though thou have time, but for a line, be that sublime. Not failure, but low aim is crime.', 1247, 0), (432970, 'It''s - everybody''s looking at the bottom line all the time, and failure doesn''t look good on the bottom line, and yet you don''t learn anything without failing.', 68949, 0), (432971, '''Catch-22'' was a huge failure, and it rubbed off on everybody connected to it. I had a bunch of lean years where I had to do things, a lot of which I wasn''t wildly enthusiastic about.', 68949, 0), (432972, 'The traditional religious right''s failure to restore public-school prayer or pass an antiabortion constitutional amendment has likely helped fuel the spread of the more extreme dominionist school.', 19516, 0), (432973, 'I buy a lot of cookbooks. Some of them you just kind of read, and you try one recipe, and it doesn''t really work. So then you don''t go back to it. The new Ina Garten cookbook, which is called ''Back to Basics,'' I have not had a failure with. It is the most fantastic cookbook. I think I bought 20 copies of it for friends.', 301, 0), (432974, 'I see disappointment as something small and aggregate rather than something unified or great. With a little effort, every failure can be turned into something good.', 229, 0), (432975, 'Being a pathfinder is to be willing to risk failure and still go on.', 30206, 0), (432976, 'Most people don''t really do too many things because they''re afraid they''ll fail. There are people failing all the time, all around you. And nobody is going to notice your failure. Your failure is not going to be so spectacular that people write news stories about it. Your failure will be boring.', 68196, 0), (432977, 'There is no middle ground in Hollywood you''re a failure or you''re a success. That mentality is wild. ', 4141, 0), (432978, 'I guess it''s the fear of failure and not knowing how the films are going to do that just drives us to work really hard to make them the best they can possibly be.', 68950, 0), (432979, 'Men are taught that if we are not the ultimate provider, we are a complete failure. We have to be number one in everything we do. There is nothing more delusional or paralysing than what I have just described.', 16258, 0), (432980, 'I feel like if we can use the combination of basically data-driven hunches and bet on really first-class talent to deliver the shows, that I think we could do as well as the networks do, who basically have a 75 to 80 percent failure rate for new shows anyway - even after all that development and pilot work.', 68951, 0), (432981, 'The power of fear of failure, with will to win, is an incredible force. I don''t think we should be worried about having a fear of failure; I think it''s quite natural. If you surveyed any top businessman or any top athlete, I bet if they were truthful, they would all say they''ve got a fear of losing and a fear of failure.', 68005, 0), (432982, 'I think I''m less afraid of failure than some others.', 11202, 0), (432983, 'People are afraid of failure - they don''t like to work so hard and have people keep saying, ''No.'' I think that''s what people fear most.', 11202, 0), (432984, 'When I was an adolescent in England, at school we had to read ''Death of a Salesman.'' I remember feeling incredibly moved by the portrayal of these people and the idea with which Miller broached the whole subject of failure or failed systems, or the way that people are crushed by a system in which they find themselves.', 68952, 0), (432985, 'Revolutionaries were depressed and close to emotional breakdown; after the failure, they left successively.', 67071, 0), (432986, 'I think, in storytelling, people want to see triumph, and so it''s usually nice to start with failure and see someone somehow rise above it. People like to see people try. And they like to see people fail for comedy, and they like to see people succeed for the drama and emotion.', 68953, 0), (432987, 'I don''t know if it''s a failure of imagination on my part, but I''m not going to be writing about Paris in the 1800s. I feel like it would come off as just ludicrously uninformed, even if I did a lot of research.', 6299, 0), (432988, 'I think if you just eat healthy, you''re active, and you don''t beat yourself up, you''re setting yourself up to win rather than setting yourself up for failure.', 68954, 0), (432989, 'In Torch Song, I did that character almost non-stop from 1978 until I made the movie in 1987. Then I had some failure, which also colors how you react to doing other things.', 1025, 0), (432990, 'All the world loves a good loser.', 14120, 0), (432991, 'It''s not that we fly by the seat of our pants. We''re not afraid of failure.', 494, 0), (432992, 'Failure worries me; nobody wants to fail. There is a fear that one day, films will not come my way, or if someone doesn''t watch your film, that is a worrying point. It is unpredictable in the industry.', 67409, 0), (432993, 'I have my way of dealing with lows in my career: I just go on a holiday. Coping with a failure of a film is like coping with a break-up. It''s sad and heart-breaking, and it''s not like I got over it right after my holiday; it took me some time.', 67409, 0), (432994, 'You''ll never convince me there is a hopeless situation or there is any finality in any success or any failure.', 66802, 0), (432995, 'In politics, what begins in fear usually ends in failure.', 1910, 0), (432996, 'Bare hands grip success better than kid gloves. Be thorough in all things, no matter how small or distasteful! The man who counts his hours and kicks about his salary is a self-elected failure.', 63087, 0), (432997, 'I don''t know which is stronger: the thrill of winning or the fear of failure. I don''t know which one affects me most. I don''t know where the middle is.', 68166, 0), (432998, 'I think I''ve failed every test I''ve ever taken. If there was a failure I would have been it.', 68955, 0), (432999, 'From a public perspective, the Grand National is the biggest race of all, and not to have won it yet is definitely a failure. But there''s been a lot of jockeys every bit as good and better than me that haven''t won it - John Francome, Peter Scudamore, Jonjo O''Neill, Charlie Swan, to name a few.', 68166, 0), (433000, 'What is more comforting to the terrorists around the world: the failure to pass the 9/11 legislation because we lacked a majority of the majority,'' or putting aside partisan politics to enact tough new legislation with America''s security foremost in mind?', 67076, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433001, 'When you can look at failure and say, ''What is the worst case scenario,'' it''s not as bad as it seems.', 68878, 0), (433002, 'Failure''s a marker of success in its own right because you went out and tried something... If you really don''t want to fail, go find a comfortable chair and stay there. Just don''t go out and do anything.', 68878, 0), (433003, 'If you truly want to find a meaningful relationship, you''ve got to find yourself first and learn to be confident in your own skin. Don''t sacrifice anything about who you are to be with someone. That''s setting yourself up for failure.', 68878, 0), (433004, 'The failure of the system to deal quickly was attributable to Nixon''s lying, stonewalling and refusal to come clean. So it took 26 months for the final truth to be known.', 16093, 0), (433005, 'One of my most vivid memories from 1974 was the gas station at the foot of the hill below my Southern California high school - car lines snaking out into the street, heralding the failure of the government''s price controls and lame ideas such as odd-even rationing.', 61422, 0), (433006, 'When you come off ''The X Factor,'' you''re more likely to be a failure than a success because people almost want you to fail. There''s this kind of feeling that you''re separate from everyone else. You get it from artists, people in the industry, people at record labels.', 68956, 0), (433007, 'I find writing very difficult. It''s hard and it hurts sometimes, and it''s scary because of the fear of failure and the very unpleasant feeling that you may have reached the limit of your abilities.', 3971, 0), (433008, 'Whenever a chef cooks for his own ego rather than his guests, he/she set themselves up for ridicule and failure. In the end, it''s the service industry. Our goal is to make our guests happy through our cooking.', 67634, 0), (433009, 'Every time you go out there to do something, you wonder if you can do it. There''s no assured success. There''s no secret recipe for success. Every time you go out there, you go out there with the possibility of great failure.', 68957, 0), (433010, 'Failure to pass TPP sends a big signal. The United States is backing off, backing away. That will create a huge void here.', 68958, 0), (433011, 'Admitting failure is quite cleansing, but never - pleasurable.', 824, 0), (433012, 'I would have thought that I would have become one of those parents - just because it''s my nature to be such a perfectionist - that anything falling short, I would have seen as a failure. But something has happened to me over the past few years - it''s not Zen, believe me, I''m not at all Zen - but I''m so appreciative of even the chaos.', 65022, 0), (433013, 'The starkest rejection letter might be followed by a million-dollar advance. Don''t let rejection start to look the same as failure.', 6948, 0), (433014, 'That sense of failure, I don''t know where people put it who don''t write songs and aren''t able to emote physically. It must go somewhere.', 9151, 0), (433015, 'Every American president must be held to the highest standard. No president of any color should be given a free pass for screw-ups, lies or failure to keep a promise.', 68674, 0), (433016, 'To me, the failure of liberalism - the tradition I come from - was not recognizing there has to be justice across the generations.', 50452, 0), (433017, 'A hatred of failure has always been part of my nature.', 11793, 0), (433018, 'So much has changed in our business. E-books, that''s been one of the principal developments. There has been also the failure of Borders and the rise of Amazon, just to name two others.', 68959, 0), (433019, 'No matter how well things are going, failure and disaster are just around the corner. So celebrate the good, but be ready for the bad.', 68872, 0), (433020, 'I have always been pushed by the negative. The apparent failure of a play sends me back to my typewriter that very night, before the reviews are out. I am more compelled to get back to work than if I had a success.', 355, 0), (433021, 'I''m fully aware that things that resonate and become real hits are the exception to the rule, so much so that I''ve wired myself for failure.', 68960, 0), (433022, 'Get used to dealing with failure as long as it doesn''t hurt people around you, as long as it doesn''t hurt you physically, or it doesn''t hurt you so much that you can''t pick yourself up.', 68867, 0), (433023, 'Success is boring... failure is exciting and more entertaining.', 67717, 0), (433024, 'I don''t think there''s any way it could have failed. We don''t know failure in this band. We didn''t know failure. We got to know it a little after awhile but at that time there was no such word.', 68473, 0), (433025, 'For market discipline to constrain risk effectively, financial institutions must be allowed to fail. Under optimal financial regulatory and financial system infrastructures, such a failure would not threaten the overall system.', 68961, 0), (433026, 'One time I nearly experienced failure was when I was acting in ''Hum Aapke Hain Kaun'' in 1994. One day, I woke up and found that part of my face was paralysed.', 67717, 0), (433027, 'It''s your own fear of failure that stops you from doing things.', 67717, 0), (433028, 'I am aware that as an actor, I can blame others for the failure of a film, the director, the script, choice of co-stars, timing of the release and so on. But now, as the director, I will have to shoulder all the blame.', 67717, 0), (433029, 'Any attempt to list the ten best science fiction novels is doomed to failure.', 28435, 0), (433030, 'War is something Arafat sends others to do for him. That is, the poor souls who believe in him. This pompous incompetent caused the failure of the Camp David negotiations, Clinton''s mediation.', 10057, 0), (433031, 'I felt a failure because I couldn''t sustain myself from what I earned from my writing. My day jobs were what mattered, and it was hard to even get those because universities wouldn''t hire me as a real writer.', 26083, 0), (433032, 'Pure unadulterated success is not as funny as failure.', 68962, 0), (433033, 'I looked long and carefully at the picture of a stag painted by Landseer - the style was good, and the brush was handled with fine effect; but he fails in copying Nature, without which the best work will be a failure.', 13434, 0), (433034, 'What I try to get physically healthy people to understand is that they''re going to die someday. There is no way out. And dying isn''t failure, but not living is, so make use of your time. Don''t keeping waiting.', 64551, 0), (433035, 'Sometimes the best gain is to lose.', 3428, 0), (433036, 'Failure usually works for me in the end.', 67705, 0), (433037, 'International aid as a means of development is a major failure, and not just in Haiti.', 68963, 0), (433038, 'The modern rise of Alzheimer''s Disease in the twentieth century is not a sign of failure. It''s a sign of success. Success in living long enough to see that disease expressed.', 68964, 0), (433039, 'I really wanted to make the worst thing: the thing that even people who liked bad, terrible music wouldn''t like - the stuff that people would ignore, always. Something really, really stupid. Something that is destined for failure.', 68965, 0), (433040, 'I was interested in political failure here in the U.S. The way we''re failing to work together to solve even our smallest problems, let alone the complex ones.', 9628, 0), (433041, 'But while success and failure depend on conditions, the mind neither waxes nor wanes.', 14298, 0), (433042, 'Those on the downside of rising economic inequality generally do not want government policies that look like handouts. They typically do not want the government to make the tax system more progressive, to impose punishing taxes on the rich, in order to give the money to them. Redistribution feels demeaning. It feels like being labeled a failure.', 67093, 0), (433043, 'Radical common sense is the wisdom gleaned from the past that recognizes the perishable opportunities of the moment. It is the willingness to admit error and the refusal to be deterred by failure.', 62855, 0), (433044, 'My father was a dreamer - my hero. He was a smart, tough guy from Poland, a cutter of lady''s handbags, an old socialist-unionist who always considered himself a failure. His big line was: ''Don''t end up like me.''', 62972, 0), (433045, 'I believe in trusting men, not only once but twice - in giving a failure another chance.', 51966, 0), (433046, 'I can''t say I''m not grateful to have journalists writing about me as a genius. But I know it''s not true. I''m not confused. I understand that success comes through a lot of failure and a lot of very embarrassing failure. People want to create the next Facebook, but they are too afraid to create the next Facemash.', 34883, 0), (433047, 'Start-ups make so many mistakes that the challenge to identify the root cause of a failure is tough. But believing in your own plan is probably the worst.', 34883, 0), (433048, 'I''ve had great success and I''ve had catastrophic failure. It''s really how you handle the rough stuff that defines you, I think.', 68966, 0), (433049, 'I''m full of self-doubt. I doubt everything I do. Everything I do is a failure.', 7863, 0), (433050, 'In the old days, variety turns like me learned how to cope with failure - we all had nights when we ''died'' on stage - but today''s youngsters simply don''t have that experience. For them, it really is instant make or break time - hence, all the tears and, hence, all the potential emotional damage.', 68967, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433051, 'Mohammed was not an apparent failure. He was a dazzling success, politically as well as spiritually, and Islam went from strength to strength to strength.', 4420, 0), (433052, 'A failure doesn''t mean you are unworthy, nor does it preclude success on the next try.', 26113, 0), (433053, 'Crime and bad lives are the measure of a State''s failure, all crime in the end is the crime of the community.', 3173, 0), (433054, 'Apple is a failure because they missed social? Nobody would say that, because they are having great success.', 66640, 0), (433055, 'I was never afraid of failure after that because, I think, coming that close to death you get kissed. With the years, the actual experience of course fades, but the flavor of it doesn''t. I just had a real sense of what choice do I have but to live fully?', 68968, 0), (433056, 'I don''t have a fear factor. Well, not much of one. And I''m willing to risk quite a lot - as a comedian, you''re always risking a lot. You''re risking failure, especially if you''re improvising and going on TV shows trying to make comedy out of thin air. That is quite a risky business.', 17043, 0), (433057, '''This Is Not That Dawn'' is remarkable in part for its careful and sensitive attention to women''s lives - and also for its harsh critique of men and their failure to stop violence.', 15932, 0), (433058, 'The thing about a failure is that it is possible to deny it forever.', 15932, 0), (433059, 'Smokey Robinson writes the heartfelt songs, whereas it was my job to write the songs about weakness and failure in love.', 9555, 0), (433060, 'Working with food was fraught with anxiety when I was a girl. Like all farmers, we were at the mercy of the weather, and we lived in fear of crop failure.', 31601, 0), (433061, 'We now live in a world where the only thing to have is success, but failure is marvelous. It''s fertiliser, it''s like living fertiliser, because you''re forced on yourself.', 68969, 0), (433062, 'It implies a slight failure as a writer that you are reduced to being a ghostwriter for the money.', 2373, 0), (433063, 'Do not blame anybody for your mistakes and failures.', 59644, 0), (433064, 'The biggest problem in my life is trying to be the kind of man that I want to be, the father that I want to be, and how to process the failure of my marriage.', 6061, 0), (433065, 'Growing up, I had the weird fantasy list: I wanted to be Alice Cooper, Steven Spielberg, and Stan Lee. You have to have almost psychotic drive, because you''re going to have years of failure.', 67097, 0), (433066, 'When I was growing up, Brandy was TV star, reality star, a pop star, a Cover girl, Grammy winner, had her own Brandy doll, and was the first African American to play Disney princess Cinderella. Most importantly, she is a survivor. Many only judge and remember a person''s most recent failure.', 68970, 0), (433067, 'Sadness is a super important thing not to be ashamed about but to include in our lives. One of the bigger problems with sadness or depression is there''s so much shame around it. If you have it you''re a failure. You are felt as being very unattractive.', 68487, 0), (433068, 'The failure of national economic policy is costing us more than jobs; it has begun to weaken that uniquely American spirit of risk-taking, large ambition, and optimism about the future. We must rally them now to bold departures that rebuild our national morale as well as our material prosperity.', 66694, 0), (433069, 'It''s not a failure if a marriage or partnership ends after a certain number of years. I think, in general, we expect too much of partners. We can''t fulfil a person''s every single need and, after ten years or so, many relationships wear out. If we were more philosophical about it, we wouldn''t try to blame the other person or be bitter.', 1428, 0), (433070, 'Case studies of failure should be made a part of the vocabulary of every engineer so that he or she can recall or recite them when something in a new design or design process is suggestive of what went wrong in the case study.', 67673, 0), (433071, 'Many of the familiar little things that we use every day have typically evolved over a period of time to a state of familiarity. They balance form and function, elegance and economy, success and failure in ways that are not only acceptable, but also admirable.', 67673, 0), (433072, 'I emphasize that virtually every engineering calculation is ultimately a failure calculation, because without a failure criterion against which to measure the calculated result, it is a meaningless number.', 67673, 0), (433073, 'I employ case studies of failure into my courses, emphasizing that they teach us much more than studies of success. It is not that success stories cannot serve as models of good design or as exemplars of creative engineering. They can do that, but they cannot teach us how close to failure they are.', 67673, 0), (433074, 'Relying on nothing but scientific knowledge to produce an engineering solution is to invite frustration at best and failure at worst.', 67673, 0), (433075, 'I''m sure not afraid of success and I''ve learned not to be afraid of failure. The only thing I''m afraid of now is of being someone I don''t like much.', 1552, 0), (433076, 'I was convicted of three misdemeanors of willful failure to file a form.', 68971, 0), (433077, 'Over the years, I learned that in my career, unlike in life, sometimes my wheelchair is its own automatic door opener. I was able to win the OWN competition by applying one simple principle: be funny, and admit you suck before anyone else can call you out on it. In other words, make the narrative of your failure a comedy.', 68492, 0), (433078, 'I''ve tried to handle winning well, so that maybe we''ll win again, but I''ve also tried to handle failure well. If those serve as good examples for teachers and kids, then I hope that would be a contribution I have made to sport. Not just basketball, but to sport.', 67885, 0), (433079, 'I think some parents now look at a youngster failing as the final thing. It''s a process, and failure is part of the process. I would like it if the teacher and the parents would connect more. I think that used to be, but we''re losing a little bit of that right now.', 67885, 0), (433080, 'If a process or adaptation seems too smart for nature, that''s a failure of your imagination, not the hand of God. I can make that claim because we have a working model of life''s morphing and molding without it.', 68972, 0), (433081, 'We are feeble, weak and impoverished because of our failure to pray. God is restrained in doing because we are restrained by reason of our non-praying. All failures in securing heaven are traceable to lack of prayer or misdirected petition.', 68973, 0), (433082, 'My great fear has always been complete and utter failure. Hence, you see, all the dispossessed people in my fiction, and why I try to earn as much money as I can. It''s a defense. I don''t enjoy it or do anything with it.', 8240, 0), (433083, 'In college football, fans wallow in a culture of failure. Unless you root for Miami, you sadly wait for disaster to strike your team in a manner not seen outside of Fenway Park.', 68974, 0), (433084, 'The higher the artist, the fewer the gestures. The fewer the tools, the greater the imagination. The greater the will, the greater the secret failure.', 1028, 0), (433085, 'The worst time was 1983. Love and life and everything went wrong. I reached absolute rock bottom. I saw the Minotaur at the bottom of the abyss. I learnt of the harshness of the world and its impartiality to human failure.', 1028, 0), (433086, 'I never feel any pressure about a film. What is meant to happen will happen. I have seen failure as well as success several times.', 67344, 0), (433087, 'If you''re 40 years old and you''ve never had a failure, you''ve been deprived.', 49634, 0), (433088, 'I have always believed that it''s important to show a new look periodically. Predictability can lead to failure.', 68975, 0), (433089, 'I''ve always believed that it''s important to show a new look periodically. Predictability can lead to failure.', 68975, 0), (433090, 'When we''re in game worlds, I believe that many of us become the best version of ourselves: the most likely to help at a moment''s notice. The most likely to stick with a problem as long as it takes. To get up after failure and try again.', 12923, 0), (433091, 'Unwillingness to risk failure is always there, but it gets harder when you feel you have more to lose.', 68976, 0), (433092, 'Yes - I am usually overweight. I have had to be interested in diet because of being diabetic for 30 years and having kidney failure.', 12949, 0), (433093, 'I think our failure as a caucus has been not to focus on economic issues. I think we - and I''m supportive of all the issues that - that we talk about, but you need an economic - a robust, economic message that - that covers everybody.', 68977, 0), (433094, 'I think that Obama''s failure to reestablish the rule of law in money matters is the most damaging thing that he''s done - and perhaps the most damaging thing that has happened in American politics in my lifetime. Because once the rule of law is absent in money matters, then anything really goes in politics.', 14299, 0), (433095, 'With the selection of Acting Secret Service Director Joseph P. Clancy as the director, President Obama has guaranteed that the agency will continue to lurch from one shocking security failure to another.', 68978, 0), (433096, 'Failure? Scared to death of it.', 66733, 0), (433097, 'I''ve learnt something from every failure. The products I helped design at the first two companies I worked for were utter failures. But now I know why.', 68979, 0), (433098, 'There''s no amount of money that makes you feel better when people think of you as a joke or a hack or a failure or ugly or stupid or morally empty.', 56632, 0), (433099, 'I have experienced failure as a politician and for that very reason, I am ready to give everything for Japan.', 67426, 0), (433100, 'When I served as prime minister last time, I failed to prioritize my agenda. I was eager to complete everything at once, and ended my administration in failure. After resigning, for six years I traveled across the nation simply to listen.', 67426, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433101, 'We learn wisdom from failure much more than from success. We often discover what will do, by finding out what will not do; and probably he who never made a mistake never made a discovery.', 7329, 0), (433102, 'We need to teach the highly educated man that it is not a disgrace to fail and that he must analyze every failure to find its cause. He must learn how to fail intelligently, for failing is one of the greatest arts in the world.', 66718, 0), (433103, 'Failure''s not a bad thing. It builds character. It makes you stronger.', 67112, 0), (433104, 'Our failings sometimes bind us to one another as closely as could virtue itself.', 64242, 0), (433105, 'Indulging in unrestrained and immoderate laughter is a sign of intemperance, of a want of control over one''s emotions, and of failure to repress the soul''s frivolity by a stern use of reason.', 63774, 0), (433106, 'Our health-care morass is like the problems of global warming and the national debt - the kind of vast policy failure that is far easier to get into than to get out of. Americans say that they want leaders who will take on these problems.', 13590, 0), (433107, 'Well, the idea is that failure is an inevitable partner on the road to success and, if you''re not willing to confront failure, you can never find out how good you are.', 68980, 0), (433108, 'Beside every great success are the seeds of enormous failure. In every failure, there''s the opportunity seeds of great success. They''re not miles apart. So if they''re that close together, and if you''re really working, you''re always gonna have that likelihood that something''s not going to work.', 68980, 0), (433109, 'Young players need freedom of expression to develop as creative players... they should be encouraged to try skills without fear of failure.', 67899, 0), (433110, 'Belief in the supernatural reflects a failure of the imagination.', 1370, 0), (433111, 'Due to the failure of politics, which has become a process of middle-management, art has become one of the last open spaces to question core beliefs and to design a viable future. Art becomes an open space where we can ask fundamental questions about ourselves.', 68029, 0), (433112, 'Failure to accord credit to anyone for what he may have done is a great weakness in any man.', 9728, 0), (433113, 'I stare out the window and reflect on the similarity between writing and saving a life and the inevitable failure of one''s imagination and one''s goals and ambitions to create a character or a life worth saving.', 4222, 0), (433114, 'Nothing helps make a leader more approachable than admitting your struggles, screw-ups and behind-the-scenes thinking on hard calls. If the leader makes this a priority, the whole company will be more open and methodical learning from failure.', 68981, 0), (433115, 'I''m not scared of anything in particular, but I am motivated by a fear of failure as opposed to a need to succeed.', 68982, 0), (433116, 'The surest way to fail is not to determine to succeed.', 20698, 0), (433117, 'Exercise, from a public health perspective, is an unmitigated failure. The world''s longest-lived people live in environments that nudge them into more movement. They don''t use power tools, they do their own yard work, they grow a garden.', 4994, 0), (433118, 'Schools don''t really allow failure and yet it''s a valid part of any endeavour, not just writing.', 27393, 0), (433119, 'In school, we learn that mistakes translate into bad grades. This unfortunate lesson gets burned into our brains, and we go through life shunning challenges that might end in failure.', 68983, 0), (433120, 'But all actors go through the process, it''s hit and miss, you have achievement and failure.', 68984, 0), (433121, 'We do not realise that we are children of eternity. If we did, then success would be no success, and failure would be no failure to us.', 68027, 0), (433122, 'Failure in Afghanistan would have profound consequences for our national security. It would undermine the NATO alliance structure that has been the bedrock of Britain''s defence for the last 60 years... I will not allow this to happen on my watch.', 68985, 0), (433123, 'I think the fall in Eden was ultimately a failure to give thanks.', 1314, 0), (433124, 'That''s the conundrum of cartoon stripping, as opposed to political cartoons. When your anger is the driving force of your drawing hand, failure follows. The anger is OK, but it has to serve the interests of the heart, frankly.', 13948, 0), (433125, 'America traditionally represents the greatest possibility of someone''s going from nothing to something. Why? In theory, if not practice, the government stays out of the way and lets individuals take risks and reap rewards or accept the consequences of failure. We call this capitalism - or, at least, we used to.', 55271, 0), (433126, 'We keep score in life because it matters. It counts. It matters. Too many people opt out and never discover their own abilities because they fear failure. They don''t understand commitment.', 33654, 0), (433127, 'I was a diabetic for 16 years, since I was 14. Being that I lost weight, no more diabetes. You don''t have to lose your eyesight, cut off your toes, have a stroke, get kidney failure. You just have to lose weight - you know - for most of the diabetes.', 68986, 0), (433128, 'The man who has done his level best... is a success, even though the world may write him down a failure.', 14130, 0), (433129, 'Right from my childhood, I have believed in a Supreme Power. I don''t know whether it has form, or it is formless. I am a high school dropout. How come life has given me so much? It''s not my intelligence, it''s not my abilities. This understanding makes me scared even in success. I don''t own my success. Neither do I own my failure.', 68849, 0), (433130, 'Total failure isn''t something I want to spend a lot of time envisioning. I''m pretty sure I''ll recognize it if it comes.', 68987, 0), (433131, 'Critics? Don''t talk to me of critics! You think some jackanapes journalist, his soul eaten away by the maggots of jealousy and failure, has anything worthwhile to say of art? I don''t.', 14150, 0), (433132, 'I have probably purchased fifty ''hot tips'' in my career, maybe even more. When I put them all together, I know I am a net loser.', 55930, 0), (433133, 'As is well known, ''McCarthyism'' was an alleged focus of political evil in the 1950s: Accusations of Communist taint, without factual basis; bogus lists of supposed Communists who never existed; failure in the end to produce even one provable Communist or Soviet agent, despite his myriad charges of subversion.', 68988, 0), (433134, 'It is easier to win than to fail. Everybody sides with the winner. But the failure walks alone.', 62529, 0), (433135, 'The hippy movement was a failure.', 11174, 0), (433136, 'You can''t let a failure keep you down, because if you stay down after you fail, you are going to stay down for good.', 67202, 0), (433137, 'Failure is what we''re all running from, we''re always running toward success with failure at our back.', 3767, 0), (433138, 'Art school had taught me it was far better to be a flamboyant failure than any kind of benign success.', 57411, 0), (433139, 'I''ve become a professional failure - in order to pay the mortgage I have to remain unemployed. Luckily, a disaster always seems to befall me at exactly the right moment.', 68989, 0), (433140, 'There is no such thing as darkness only a failure to see. ', 9186, 0), (433141, 'Some teachers feel that if they ask for emotional help, they''re a failure. But teaching is a team sport.', 30637, 0), (433142, 'I think success has no rules, but you can learn a great deal from failure.', 2403, 0), (433143, 'The failure to read good books both enfeebles the vision and strengthens our most fatal tendency - the belief that the here and now is all there is.', 2791, 0), (433144, 'Is anarchism possible? The failure of attempts to attain freedom does not mean the cause is lost.', 68990, 0), (433145, 'At first I wasn''t sure that I had the talent, but I did know I had a fear of failure, and that fear compelled me to fight off anything that might abet it.', 68991, 0), (433146, 'I''m not an artist, and I want to take risks, and when the possibility of failure occurs, it''s because the idea is all exciting or interesting as a high wire act, and sometimes you''ve got to fall off, just by virtue of the fact that you''re constantly trying to evolve and do new things.', 17571, 0), (433147, 'In God''s world, for those who are in earnest, there is no failure. No work truly done, no word earnestly spoken, no sacrifice freely made, was ever made in vain.', 68992, 0), (433148, 'Without exposure to potential failure, there is no risk.', 575, 0), (433149, 'I have a tendency to sabotage relationships; I have a tendency to sabotage everything. Fear of success, fear of failure, fear of being afraid. Useless, good-for-nothing thoughts.', 68387, 0), (433150, 'When I was 18, I couldn''t wait to move away. I was like: ''If I ever have to come back here, I''ll kill myself.'' Glasgow seemed like failure and death to me back then, but not any more.', 15445, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433151, 'The world is divided into two categories: failures and unknowns.', 51603, 0), (433152, 'If the whole process of learning from failure means discarding stuff that''s not working, but in fact, our natural reaction is to keep going, to throw more money behind it, to throw more emotional energy behind it... that''s a real problem.', 32773, 0), (433153, 'I was learning the craft; I didn''t study writing in school. Rejection was my motivation, and failure is what taught me.', 3963, 0), (433154, 'I love language, and I love the failure of language.', 68993, 0), (433155, 'The U.S. has a law on the books called the debt limit, but the name is misleading. The debt limit started in 1917 for the purpose of facilitating more national debt, not reducing it. It still serves that purpose. It''s unconnected to spending, hurts our credit rating and has been an abject failure at limiting debt.', 68994, 0), (433156, 'Catastrophes are often stimulated by the failure to feel the emergence of a domain, and so what cannot be felt in the imagination is experienced as embodied sensation in the catastrophe.', 68995, 0), (433157, 'I couldn''t stand the thought of not succeeding failure was more than I could deal with. ', 68996, 0), (433158, 'What we have most to fear is failure of the heart.', 18469, 0), (433159, 'I''m fascinated by failure, and I''m fascinated by finality. Shakespeare''s historical plays are more universal than his comedies because they relate to the finality of life. Without finality, life would not be beautiful.', 68997, 0), (433160, 'You must not demand the failure of your peers, because the more good things that are around in film, in television, in theater - why the better it is for all of us.', 12908, 0), (433161, 'Having in my life been bitten by the jaws of both victory and defeat, I must rush to add that success is to failure as butter pecan ice cream is to death.', 68998, 0), (433162, 'If you don''t accept failure as a possibility, you don''t set high goals, you don''t branch out, you don''t try - you don''t take the risk.', 19480, 0), (433163, 'I never see failure as failure, but only as the game I must play and win.', 46512, 0), (433164, 'All that is necessary to break the spell of inertia and frustration is this: Act as if it were impossible to fail. That is the talisman, the formula, the command of right about face which turns us from failure to success.', 40351, 0), (433165, 'The success or failure of a life, as far as posterity goes, seems to lie in the more or less luck of seizing the right moment of escape.', 3447, 0), (433166, 'Notice the difference between what happens when a man says to himself, I have failed three times, and what happens when he says, I am a failure.', 20148, 0), (433167, 'Mr. Gonzales'' failure to respond to questions legitimately posed to him by the Senate raises grave doubts in my mind as to his fitness to serve the people of the United States as their Attorney General.', 67410, 0), (433168, 'Entrepreneurs are risk takers, willing to roll the dice with their money or reputation on the line in support of an idea or enterprise. They willingly assume responsibility for the success or failure of a venture and are answerable for all its facets.', 9614, 0), (433169, 'The assertion of failure coming from such persons does not mean that Mr. Mill failed to promote the practical success of those objects the advocacy of which forms the chief feature of his political writings.', 68999, 0), (433170, 'Losing is no disgrace if you''ve given your best.', 36696, 0), (433171, 'Any man who has $10,000 left when he dies is a failure.', 69000, 0), (433172, 'I''ve criticized President Bush for his failure to use his veto pen. There''s plenty of blame to go around. The question is how to solve problems. It''s not bailouts. What made America great? Free markets, free enterprise, manufacturing, job creation. That''s how we''re gonna do it, not by enlarging government.', 67316, 0), (433173, 'Divorce is never a pleasant experience. You look upon it as a failure. But I learned to be a different person once we broke up. Sometimes you learn more from failure than you do from success.', 68901, 0), (433174, 'Spend enough time around success and failure, and you learn a reverence for possibility.', 64583, 0), (433175, 'I wasn''t afraid to fail. Something good always comes out of failure.', 68844, 0), (433176, 'Success and failure are greatly overrated. But failure gives you a whole lot more to talk about.', 69001, 0), (433177, 'It really is impossible not to like him. His success was his failure.', 3150, 0), (433178, 'The failure of women to have reached positions of leadership has been due in large part to social and professional discrimination.', 69002, 0), (433179, 'Most social acts have to be understood in their setting and lose meaning if isolated... No error in thinking about social facts is more serious than the failure to see their place and function.', 69003, 0), (433180, 'Love yourself. It is important to stay positive because beauty comes from the inside out.', 69004, 0), (433181, 'Success is no accident. It is hard work, perseverance, learning, studying, sacrifice and most of all, love of what you are doing or learning to do.', 12296, 0), (433182, 'Friends show their love in times of trouble, not in happiness.', 542, 0), (433183, 'Love myself I do. Not everything, but I love the good as well as the bad. I love my crazy lifestyle, and I love my hard discipline. I love my freedom of speech and the way my eyes get dark when I''m tired. I love that I have learned to trust people with my heart, even if it will get broken. I am proud of everything that I am and will become.', 37495, 0), (433184, 'Immature love says: ''I love you because I need you.'' Mature love says ''I need you because I love you.''', 190, 0), (433185, 'Love is friendship that has caught fire. It is quiet understanding, mutual confidence, sharing and forgiving. It is loyalty through good and bad times. It settles for less than perfection and makes allowances for human weaknesses.', 3199, 0), (433186, 'Sometimes the heart sees what is invisible to the eye.', 63634, 0), (433187, 'There is no love without forgiveness, and there is no forgiveness without love.', 24882, 0), (433188, 'Peace is the beauty of life. It is sunshine. It is the smile of a child, the love of a mother, the joy of a father, the togetherness of a family. It is the advancement of man, the victory of a just cause, the triumph of truth.', 68756, 0), (433189, 'A successful marriage requires falling in love many times, always with the same person.', 1932, 0), (433190, 'Keep love in your heart. A life without it is like a sunless garden when the flowers are dead.', 40, 0), (433191, 'The beauty of a woman must be seen from in her eyes, because that is the doorway to her heart, the place where love resides.', 999, 0), (433192, 'Love isn''t something you find. Love is something that finds you.', 44815, 0), (433193, 'Work like you don''t need the money. Love like you''ve never been hurt. Dance like nobody''s watching.', 5228, 0), (433194, 'If you love someone, set them free. If they come back they''re yours; if they don''t they never were.', 424, 0), (433195, 'Beauty is when you can appreciate yourself. When you love yourself, that''s when you''re most beautiful.', 68464, 0), (433196, 'Nobody can predict the future. You just have to give your all to the relationship you''re in and do your best to take care of your partner, communicate and give them every last drop of love you have. I think one of the most important things in a relationship is caring for your significant other through good times and bad.', 67879, 0), (433197, 'Choose a job you love, and you will never have to work a day in your life.', 819, 0), (433198, 'If you love life, don''t waste time, for time is what life is made up of.', 510, 0), (433199, 'Darkness cannot drive out darkness only light can do that. Hate cannot drive out hate only love can do that. ', 21767, 0), (433200, 'I love you the more in that I believe you had liked me for my own sake and for nothing else.', 191, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433201, 'The good life is one inspired by love and guided by knowledge.', 95, 0), (433202, 'Did I offer peace today? Did I bring a smile to someone''s face? Did I say words of healing? Did I let go of my anger and resentment? Did I forgive? Did I love? These are the real questions. I must trust that the little bit of love that I sow now will bear many fruits, here in this world and the life to come.', 19097, 0), (433203, 'Love will find a way through paths where wolves fear to prey.', 62558, 0), (433204, 'True love cannot be found where it does not exist, nor can it be denied where it does.', 915, 0), (433205, 'The greatest gift that you can give to others is the gift of unconditional love and acceptance.', 697, 0), (433206, 'You can never control who you fall in love with, even when you''re in the most sad, confused time of your life. You don''t fall in love with people because they''re fun. It just happens.', 68430, 0), (433207, 'True love stories never have endings.', 424, 0), (433208, 'Let the beauty of what you love be what you do.', 20453, 0), (433209, 'We''re born alone, we live alone, we die alone. Only through our love and friendship can we create the illusion for the moment that we''re not alone.', 1256, 0), (433210, 'Study nature, love nature, stay close to nature. It will never fail you.', 1836, 0), (433211, 'Friends can help each other. A true friend is someone who lets you have total freedom to be yourself - and especially to feel. Or, not feel. Whatever you happen to be feeling at the moment is fine with them. That''s what real love amounts to - letting a person be what he really is.', 216, 0), (433212, 'A flower cannot blossom without sunshine, and man cannot live without love.', 69005, 0), (433213, 'I am good, but not an angel. I do sin, but I am not the devil. I am just a small girl in a big world trying to find someone to love.', 1, 0), (433214, 'Liza, I love you more than any words can say. You have made me a complete person. You are everything to me. And I cannot think of living life without you. And I love you forever.', 69006, 0), (433215, 'A dog is the only thing on earth that loves you more than you love yourself.', 3355, 0), (433216, 'When you arise in the morning, think of what a precious privilege it is to be alive - to breathe, to think, to enjoy, to love.', 267, 0), (433217, 'Unconditional love really exists in each of us. It is part of our deep inner being. It is not so much an active emotion as a state of being. It''s not ''I love you'' for this or that reason, not ''I love you if you love me.'' It''s love for no reason, love without an object.', 1853, 0), (433218, 'I see Americans of every party, every background, every faith who believe that we are stronger together: black, white, Latino, Asian, Native American; young, old; gay, straight; men, women, folks with disabilities, all pledging allegiance under the same proud flag to this big, bold country that we love. That''s what I see. That''s the America I know!', 1693, 0), (433219, 'Happiness cannot be traveled to, owned, earned, worn or consumed. Happiness is the spiritual experience of living every minute with love, grace, and gratitude.', 1391, 0), (433220, 'Music is love, love is music, music is life, and I love my life. Thank you and good night.', 69007, 0), (433221, 'Who so loves believes the impossible.', 157, 0), (433222, 'You can''t blame gravity for falling in love.', 104, 0), (433223, 'Love the art in yourself and not yourself in the art.', 69008, 0), (433224, 'Never make a decision when you are upset, sad, jealous or in love.', 68843, 0), (433225, 'When the power of love overcomes the love of power the world will know peace.', 92, 0), (433226, 'A grateful heart is a beginning of greatness. It is an expression of humility. It is a foundation for the development of such virtues as prayer, faith, courage, contentment, happiness, love, and well-being.', 9153, 0), (433227, 'Black as the devil, hot as hell, pure as an angel, sweet as love.', 59960, 0), (433228, 'A tree is known by its fruit; a man by his deeds. A good deed is never lost; he who sows courtesy reaps friendship, and he who plants kindness gathers love.', 63774, 0), (433229, 'True love is like ghosts, which everyone talks about and few have seen.', 154, 0), (433230, 'A birthday is just another day where you go to work and people give you love. Age is just a state of mind, and you are as old as you think you are. You have to count your blessings and be happy.', 67107, 0), (433231, 'Mama was my greatest teacher, a teacher of compassion, love and fearlessness. If love is sweet as a flower, then my mother is that sweet flower of love.', 2141, 0), (433232, 'Love is composed of a single soul inhabiting two bodies.', 1116, 0), (433233, 'You need a strong family because at the end, they will love you and support you unconditionally. Luckily, I have my dad, mom and sister.', 69009, 0), (433234, 'I love the feeling of the fresh air on my face and the wind blowing through my hair.', 67044, 0), (433235, 'Love and compassion are necessities, not luxuries. Without them humanity cannot survive.', 5025, 0), (433236, 'Men always want to be a woman''s first love - women like to be a man''s last romance.', 40, 0), (433237, 'Love is a mutual self-giving which ends in self-recovery.', 911, 0), (433238, 'Red is such an interesting color to correlate with emotion, because it''s on both ends of the spectrum. On one end you have happiness, falling in love, infatuation with someone, passion, all that. On the other end, you''ve got obsession, jealousy, danger, fear, anger and frustration.', 100, 0), (433239, 'The most important thing a father can do for his children is to love their mother.', 50085, 0), (433240, 'The regret of my life is that I have not said ''I love you'' often enough.', 1121, 0), (433241, 'Love me or hate me, both are in my favour. If you love me, I will always be in your heart, and if you hate me, I will be in your mind.', 69010, 0), (433242, 'Money can buy you a fine dog, but only love can make him wag his tail.', 3584, 0), (433243, 'Don''t ever criticize yourself. Don''t go around all day long thinking, ''I''m unattractive, I''m slow, I''m not as smart as my brother.'' God wasn''t having a bad day when he made you... If you don''t love yourself in the right way, you can''t love your neighbour. You can''t be as good as you are supposed to be.', 3956, 0), (433244, 'Rare as is true love, true friendship is rarer.', 2843, 0), (433245, 'Love is the answer, and you know that for sure; Love is a flower, you''ve got to let it grow.', 46, 0), (433246, 'The secret of a happy marriage is finding the right person. You know they''re right if you love to be with them all the time.', 1537, 0), (433247, 'We must develop and maintain the capacity to forgive. He who is devoid of the power to forgive is devoid of the power to love. There is some good in the worst of us and some evil in the best of us. When we discover this, we are less prone to hate our enemies.', 21767, 0), (433248, 'I am in you and you in me, mutual in divine love.', 221, 0), (433249, 'True love doesn''t happen right away; it''s an ever-growing process. It develops after you''ve gone through many ups and downs, when you''ve suffered together, cried together, laughed together.', 69011, 0), (433250, 'Spread love everywhere you go. Let no one ever come to you without leaving happier.', 70, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433251, 'There is pleasure in the pathless woods, there is rapture in the lonely shore, there is society where none intrudes, by the deep sea, and music in its roar; I love not Man the less, but Nature more.', 62558, 0), (433252, 'I love fashion, and I love changing my style, my hair, my makeup, and everything I''ve done in the past has made me what I am now. Not everyone is going to like what I do, but I look back at everything, and it makes me smile.', 67831, 0), (433253, 'The love of family and the admiration of friends is much more important than wealth and privilege.', 37230, 0), (433254, 'Love of beauty is taste. The creation of beauty is art.', 760, 0), (433255, 'Love who you are, embrace who you are. Love yourself. When you love yourself, people can kind of pick up on that: they can see confidence, they can see self-esteem, and naturally, people gravitate towards you.', 68220, 0), (433256, 'Where we love is home - home that our feet may leave, but not our hearts.', 24754, 0), (433257, 'Love grows more tremendously full, swift, poignant, as the years multiply.', 16694, 0), (433258, 'There is a sacredness in tears. They are not the mark of weakness, but of power. They speak more eloquently than ten thousand tongues. They are the messengers of overwhelming grief, of deep contrition, and of unspeakable love.', 944, 0), (433259, 'I love you - I am at rest with you - I have come home.', 3165, 0), (433260, 'A wedding anniversary is the celebration of love, trust, partnership, tolerance and tenacity. The order varies for any given year.', 2530, 0), (433261, 'Go after what you really love and find a way to make that work for you, and then you''ll be a happy person.', 21291, 0), (433262, 'There is no sincerer love than the love of food.', 266, 0), (433263, 'Don''t aim for success if you want it; just do what you love and believe in, and it will come naturally.', 5472, 0), (433264, 'We, the People, recognize that we have responsibilities as well as rights; that our destinies are bound together; that a freedom which only asks what''s in it for me, a freedom without a commitment to others, a freedom without love or charity or duty or patriotism, is unworthy of our founding ideals, and those who died in their defense.', 1693, 0), (433265, 'A dog will teach you unconditional love. If you can have that in your life, things won''t be too bad.', 69012, 0), (433266, 'My friends and family are my support system. They tell me what I need to hear, not what I want to hear and they are there for me in the good and bad times. Without them I have no idea where I would be and I know that their love for me is what''s keeping my head above the water.', 9111, 0), (433267, 'The human soul is hungry for beauty; we seek it everywhere - in landscape, music, art, clothes, furniture, gardening, companionship, love, religion, and in ourselves. No one would desire not to be beautiful. When we experience the beautiful, there is a sense of homecoming.', 400, 0), (433268, 'We can bring positive energy into our daily lives by smiling more, talking to strangers in line, replacing handshakes with hugs, and calling our friends just to tell them we love them.', 66950, 0), (433269, 'Love is when he gives you a piece of your soul, that you never knew was missing.', 915, 0), (433270, 'Love yourself first and everything else falls into line. You really have to love yourself to get anything done in this world.', 1814, 0), (433271, 'I think every girl needs to love herself, regardless of anything. Like if you''re having a bad day, if you don''t like your hair, if you don''t have the best family situation, whatever, you have to love yourself and you can''t do anything until you love yourself first.', 69013, 0), (433272, 'Love is an act of endless forgiveness, a tender look which becomes a habit.', 2206, 0), (433273, 'You, yourself, as much as anybody in the entire universe, deserve your love and affection.', 63441, 0), (433274, 'Pursue some path, however narrow and crooked, in which you can walk with love and reverence.', 1049, 0), (433275, 'I have decided to stick with love. Hate is too great a burden to bear.', 21767, 0), (433276, 'Love is the flower you''ve got to let grow.', 46, 0), (433277, 'Love has a tide!', 25904, 0), (433278, 'We love life, not because we are used to living but because we are used to loving.', 11, 0), (433279, 'Slavery is founded in the selfishness of man''s nature - opposition to it is his love of justice. These principles are an eternal antagonism; and when brought into collision so fiercely, as slavery extension brings them, shocks and throes and convulsions must ceaselessly follow.', 1012, 0), (433280, 'Religion is meant to teach us true spiritual human character. It is meant for self-transformation. It is meant to transform anxiety into peace, arrogance into humility, envy into compassion, to awaken the pure soul in man and his love for the Source, which is God.', 26105, 0), (433281, 'I love you, and because I love you, I would sooner have you hate me for telling you the truth than adore me for telling you lies.', 62366, 0), (433282, 'Grief can be the garden of compassion. If you keep your heart open through everything, your pain can become your greatest ally in your life''s search for love and wisdom.', 20453, 0), (433283, 'We should remember that saying ''I love you'' is only a beginning. We need to say it, we need to mean it, and most importantly we need consistently to show it. We need to both express and demonstrate love.', 11448, 0), (433284, 'A flower doesn''t love you or hate you, it just exists.', 69014, 0), (433285, 'If you have only one smile in you give it to the people you love.', 74, 0), (433286, 'But let there be spaces in your togetherness and let the winds of the heavens dance between you. Love one another but make not a bond of love: let it rather be a moving sea between the shores of your souls.', 5542, 0), (433287, 'We are born of love, Love is our mother. ', 20453, 0), (433288, 'You''re not looking for perfection in your partner. Perfection is all about the ego. With soulmate love, you know that true love is what happens when disappointment sets in - and you''re willing to deal maturely with these disappointments.', 5238, 0), (433289, 'A new command I give you: Love one another. As I have loved you, so you must love one another.', 17018, 0), (433290, 'Love planted a rose, and the world turned sweet.', 62482, 0), (433291, 'Be Impeccable With Your Word. Speak with integrity. Say only what you mean. Avoid using the word to speak against yourself or to gossip about others. Use the power of your word in the direction of truth and love.', 67703, 0), (433292, 'If we''re destroying our trees and destroying our environment and hurting animals and hurting one another and all that stuff, there''s got to be a very powerful energy to fight that. I think we need more love in the world. We need more kindness, more compassion, more joy, more laughter. I definitely want to contribute to that.', 1217, 0), (433293, 'What I love most about this crazy life is the adventure of it.', 69015, 0), (433294, 'Love is the master key that opens the gates of happiness, of hatred, of jealousy, and, most easily of all, the gate of fear.', 24754, 0), (433295, 'One way to feel good about yourself is to love yourself... to take care of yourself.', 1245, 0), (433296, 'Love begins at home, and it is not how much we do... but how much love we put in that action.', 70, 0), (433297, 'God wants us to know that life is a series of beginnings, not endings. Just as graduations are not terminations, but commencements. Creation is an ongoing process, and when we create a perfect world where love and compassion are shared by all, suffering will cease.', 64551, 0), (433298, 'Be happy with being you. Love your flaws. Own your quirks. And know that you are just as perfect as anyone else, exactly as you are.', 52532, 0), (433299, 'There would be no need for love if perfection were possible. Love arises from our imperfection, from our being different and always in need of the forgiveness, encouragement and that missing half of ourselves that we are searching for, as the Greek myth tells us, in order to complete ourselves.', 56265, 0), (433300, 'Christmas is the perfect time to celebrate the love of God and family and to create memories that will last forever. Jesus is God''s perfect, indescribable gift. The amazing thing is that not only are we able to receive this gift, but we are able to share it with others on Christmas and every other day of the year.', 3956, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433301, 'I love spending time with my friends and family. The simplest things in life give me the most pleasure: cooking a good meal, enjoying my friends.', 69016, 0), (433302, 'Marriage is not a noun it''s a verb. It isn''t something you get. It''s something you do. It''s the way you love your partner every day. ', 28913, 0), (433303, 'Love is flower like Friendship is like a sheltering tree. ', 1910, 0), (433304, 'Never go on trips with anyone you do not love.', 110, 0), (433305, 'Lord, make me an instrument of thy peace. Where there is hatred, let me sow love.', 1681, 0), (433306, 'I love you more than my own skin.', 1759, 0), (433307, 'Love looks not with the eyes, but with the mind, And therefore is winged Cupid painted blind.', 13, 0), (433308, 'Joy is prayer joy is strength: joy is love joy is a net of love by which you can catch souls. ', 70, 0), (433309, 'I love to sit on a mountain top and gaze. I don''t think of anything but the people I care about and the view.', 69017, 0), (433310, 'I love the sounds and the power of pounding water, whether it is the waves or a waterfall.', 69018, 0), (433311, 'The most powerful weapon on earth is the human soul on fire.', 14580, 0), (433312, 'An anniversary is a reminder as to why you love and married this person.', 69019, 0), (433313, 'The garden of love is green without limit and yields many fruits other than sorrow or joy. Love is beyond either condition: without spring, without autumn, it is always fresh.', 20453, 0), (433314, 'Never forget the three powerful resources you always have available to you: love, prayer, and forgiveness.', 63634, 0), (433315, 'Love is an ice cream sundae, with all the marvelous coverings. Sex is the cherry on top.', 23263, 0), (433316, 'Life in common among people who love each other is the ideal of happiness.', 810, 0), (433317, 'I believe in Liberty for all men: the space to stretch their arms and their souls, the right to breathe and the right to vote, the freedom to choose their friends, enjoy the sunshine, and ride on the railroads, uncursed by color; thinking, dreaming, working as they will in a kingdom of beauty and love.', 3227, 0), (433318, 'A deep sense of love and belonging is an irreducible need of all people. We are biologically, cognitively, physically, and spiritually wired to love, to be loved, and to belong. When those needs are not met, we don''t function as we were meant to. We break. We fall apart. We numb. We ache. We hurt others. We get sick.', 247, 0), (433319, 'Culture is the intersection of people and life itself. It''s how we deal with life, love, death, birth, disappointment... all of that is expressed in culture.', 69020, 0), (433320, 'I have my own high standards for what I want in a partner and how I want to be treated. I bring a lot to the table. I''m not talking about material things but what I have to offer as a person - love and loyalty and all the things that make a good relationship.', 24514, 0), (433321, 'True love is selfless. It is prepared to sacrifice.', 69021, 0), (433322, 'I really just want to be warm yellow light that pours over everyone I love.', 69022, 0), (433323, 'I really love to ride my motorcycle. When I want to just get away and be by myself and clear my head, that''s what I do.', 68488, 0), (433324, '''Tis better to have loved and lost than never to have loved at all.', 63203, 0), (433325, 'Using social media to hurt and destroy is callous, acted out by cowards hiding behind computers. My advice is to ignore negativity. Focus on the love around.', 68111, 0), (433326, 'Love is blind friendship closes its eyes. ', 11, 0), (433327, 'Enlightened leadership is spiritual if we understand spirituality not as some kind of religious dogma or ideology but as the domain of awareness where we experience values like truth, goodness, beauty, love and compassion, and also intuition, creativity, insight and focused attention.', 1194, 0), (433328, 'If you do what you love, it is the best way to relax.', 18155, 0), (433329, 'Thank you, God, for this good life and forgive us if we do not love it enough.', 1205, 0), (433330, 'I think in a lot of ways unconditional love is a myth. My mom''s the only reason I know it''s a real thing.', 69022, 0), (433331, 'What we have once enjoyed we can never lose. All that we love deeply becomes a part of us.', 701, 0), (433332, 'Winners embrace hard work. They love the discipline of it, the trade-off they''re making to win. Losers, on the other hand, see it as punishment. And that''s the difference.', 2081, 0), (433333, 'You can search throughout the entire universe for someone who is more deserving of your love and affection than you are yourself, and that person is not to be found anywhere. You yourself, as much as anybody in the entire universe deserve your love and affection.', 63441, 0), (433334, 'We''ve got this gift of love, but love is like a precious plant. You can''t just accept it and leave it in the cupboard or just think it''s going to get on by itself. You''ve got to keep watering it. You''ve got to really look after it and nurture it.', 46, 0), (433335, 'Life is a game and true love is a trophy.', 8055, 0), (433336, 'A dream is what makes people love life even when it is painful.', 51760, 0), (433337, 'Every age has its storytelling form, and video gaming is a huge part of our culture. You can ignore or embrace video games and imbue them with the best artistic quality. People are enthralled with video games in the same way as other people love the cinema or theatre.', 69023, 0), (433338, 'You give loyalty, you''ll get it back. You give love, you''ll get it back.', 5198, 0), (433339, 'I believe in soulmates, yes, but I believe you also have to work at love. I happen to believe your soulmate doesn''t have to be your partner - your soulmate could be your best friend, your sibling, it doesn''t have to be the person you marry.', 45064, 0), (433340, 'Love is the most important thing in the world, but baseball is pretty good, too.', 1896, 0), (433341, 'I absolutely love spending time with my family.', 69024, 0), (433342, 'If you do what you love, you''ll never work a day in your life.', 69025, 0), (433343, 'I love that feeling of being in love, the effect of having butterflies when you wake up in the morning. That is special.', 883, 0), (433344, 'Dare, dream, dance, smile, and sing loudly! And have faith that love is an unstoppable force!', 6512, 0), (433345, 'Communism is not love. Communism is a hammer which we use to crush the enemy.', 15795, 0), (433346, 'I spent a lot of years trying to outrun or outsmart vulnerability by making things certain and definite, black and white, good and bad. My inability to lean into the discomfort of vulnerability limited the fullness of those important experiences that are wrought with uncertainty: Love, belonging, trust, joy, and creativity to name a few.', 247, 0), (433347, 'The story of life is quicker than the blink of an eye, the story of love is hello, goodbye.', 92, 0), (433348, 'I love the smell of rain, and I love the sound of the ocean waves.', 68264, 0), (433349, 'Intense love does not measure, it just gives.', 70, 0), (433350, 'What I am is how I came out. No one''s perfect and you just have to accept your flaws and learn to love yourself.', 69026, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433351, 'Life is the flower for which love is the honey.', 98, 0), (433352, 'Man must evolve for all human conflict a method which rejects revenge, aggression and retaliation. The foundation of such a method is love.', 21767, 0), (433353, 'I love the spirit of Halloween and the energy that comes with it.', 69027, 0), (433354, 'With me, what you see is what you get. Yes, call me naive, but I love life. I am happy, and for that, I make no apologies. I do like to see the best in people, and when someone is nice to my face, I tend to believe them.', 69028, 0), (433355, 'What does love look like? It has the hands to help others. It has the feet to hasten to the poor and needy. It has eyes to see misery and want. It has the ears to hear the sighs and sorrows of men. That is what love looks like.', 63060, 0), (433356, 'Doubt thou the stars are fire, Doubt that the sun doth move. Doubt truth to be a liar, But never doubt I love.', 13, 0), (433357, 'Singing is my passion, my first love and the secret of my energy. Music to me is like finding my inner self, my soul. It gives me a great joy to see audiences enjoying with me. I have given my heart to singing. When I sing, I can feel romance in everything around me.', 69029, 0), (433358, 'Love begins by taking care of the closest ones - the ones at home.', 70, 0), (433359, 'Never trust anyone completely but God. Love people, but put your full trust only in God.', 13165, 0), (433360, 'Experts on romance say for a happy marriage there has to be more than a passionate love. For a lasting union, they insist, there must be a genuine liking for each other. Which, in my book, is a good definition for friendship.', 1, 0), (433361, 'I''m not ashamed to be me. More than anyone else I know, I love my life and accept myself. What''s wrong with being unique? I am proud of everything that I am and will become.', 37495, 0), (433362, 'To know yourself as the Being underneath the thinker, the stillness underneath the mental noise, the love and joy underneath the pain, is freedom, salvation, enlightenment.', 378, 0), (433363, 'I thank God that I''m a product of my parents. That they infected me with their intelligence and energy for life, with their thirst for knowledge and their love. I''m grateful that I know where I come from.', 67847, 0), (433364, 'Since love grows within you, so beauty grows. For love is the beauty of the soul.', 63060, 0), (433365, 'Life without love is like a tree without blossoms or fruit.', 5542, 0), (433366, 'My favorite thing about motherhood is the outpouring of love that is non-judgmental and beautiful. My daughter just makes me happy, and she motivates me to be a kid again.', 67850, 0), (433367, 'Mother''s love is peace. It need not be acquired, it need not be deserved.', 190, 0), (433368, 'I knew I was going to love my daughter, but I had no idea how much I would love her.', 69030, 0), (433369, 'My sister is a mess. I love her to death, but she is a mess.', 69031, 0), (433370, 'You might not make it to the top, but if you are doing what you love, there is much more happiness there than being rich or famous.', 54545, 0), (433371, 'I love deadlines. I like the whooshing sound they make as they fly by.', 386, 0), (433372, 'But the love of adventure was in father''s blood.', 69032, 0), (433373, 'I need to see my own beauty and to continue to be reminded that I am enough, that I am worthy of love without effort, that I am beautiful, that the texture of my hair and that the shape of my curves, the size of my lips, the color of my skin, and the feelings that I have are all worthy and okay.', 69033, 0), (433374, 'The minute I heard my first love story, I started looking for you, not knowing how blind that was. Lovers don''t finally meet somewhere. They''re in each other all along.', 20453, 0), (433375, 'No one can make you happy. No one can help you grow in life more than you can. I can love you to death, but I can only go so far. I can inspire and encourage you as much as I can, but when you play an active role to find that self-security and that self-worth, it makes the difference.', 69034, 0), (433376, 'Love doesn''t make the world go ''round. Love is what makes the ride worthwhile.', 62728, 0), (433377, 'My eye is ever on those who love me.', 29441, 0), (433378, 'In life, you have to take the pace that love goes. You don''t force it. You just don''t force love, you don''t force falling in love, you don''t force being in love - you just become. I don''t know how to say that in English, but you just feel it.', 59657, 0), (433379, 'You just have to get rid of fear and confront the world. Look at yourself in the mirror and say to yourself, ''I love you and nothing will destroy you and you''re not going to fall.''', 67432, 0), (433380, 'In the stillness of your presence, you can feel your own formless and timeless reality as the unmanifested life that animates your physical form. You can then feel the same life deep within every other human and every other creature. You look beyond the veil of form and separation. This is the realization of oneness. This is love.', 378, 0), (433381, 'If you love somebody, let them go, for if they return, they were always yours. And if they don''t, they never were.', 5542, 0), (433382, 'I love it when people doubt me. It makes me work harder to prove them wrong.', 66702, 0), (433383, 'We are supposed to enjoy the good stuff now, while we can, with the people we love. Life has a funny way of teaching us that lesson over and over again.', 69035, 0), (433384, 'I trust you: That''s huge. That''s truth. That''s real love. Everyone uses ''I love you'' so loosely.', 69036, 0), (433385, 'The beginning of love is to let those we love be perfectly themselves, and not to twist them to fit our own image. Otherwise we love only the reflection of ourselves we find in them.', 123, 0), (433386, 'We are not the same persons this year as last; nor are those we love. It is a happy chance if we, changing, continue to love a changed person.', 235, 0), (433387, 'In my life I''ve learned that true happiness comes from giving. Helping others along the way makes you evaluate who you are. I think that love is what we''re all searching for. I haven''t come across anyone who didn''t become a better person through love.', 69037, 0), (433388, 'We may not know what each day has in store for us. We could be gone tomorrow. Any minute could truly be our goodbye. But we do have this moment. This time. Today. Right now. It takes way more effort to shell out hate then it does to allow love to flow freely in our lives. After all, it''s what we were born to do.', 67459, 0), (433389, 'Patriotism is when love of your own people comes first; nationalism, when hate for people other than your own comes first.', 11599, 0), (433390, 'Friendship is certainly the finest balm for the pangs of disappointed love.', 24, 0), (433391, 'The thing is that love gives us a ringside seat on somebody else''s flaws, so of course you''re gonna spot some things that kinda need to be mentioned. But often the romantic view is to say, ''If you loved me, you wouldn''t criticise me.'' Actually, true love is often about trying to teach someone how to be the best version of themselves.', 639, 0), (433392, 'Love one another and help others to rise to the higher levels, simply by pouring out love. Love is infectious and the greatest healing energy.', 29441, 0), (433393, 'Every one has her own love life. Every one has a dream to get a perfect life partner. But this is not so easy in real life. In fact, one doesn''t love; it happens.', 66894, 0), (433394, 'Love is friendship set on fire.', 3943, 0), (433395, 'True love is not a strong, fiery, impetuous passion. It is, on the contrary, an element calm and deep. It looks beyond mere externals, and is attracted by qualities alone. It is wise and discriminating, and its devotion is real and abiding.', 4150, 0), (433396, 'Yes, it was love at first sight. I feel that after all these years, I have finally found my soul mate.', 62514, 0), (433397, 'Going home, spending time with the family, I feel they''re my friends as well, all of them. I look forward to meeting any one of them for a coffee, and when we all get together, I just love it.', 68286, 0), (433398, 'Power is of two kinds. One is obtained by the fear of punishment and the other by acts of love. Power based on love is a thousand times more effective and permanent then the one derived from fear of punishment.', 32, 0), (433399, 'Love is the silent saying and saying of a single name.', 1932, 0), (433400, 'You''ve got to love yourself first. You''ve got to be okay on your own before you can be okay with somebody else.', 24514, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433401, 'Believe in yourself, listen to your gut, and do what you love.', 69038, 0), (433402, 'Hunting forces a person to endure, to master themselves, even to truly get to know the wild environment. Actually, along the way, hunting and fishing makes you fall in love with the natural world. This is why hunters so often give back by contributing to conservation.', 64643, 0), (433403, 'When you love and accept yourself, when you know who really cares about you, and when you learn from your mistakes, then you stop caring about what people who don''t know you think.', 1525, 0), (433404, 'Motherhood: All love begins and ends there.', 698, 0), (433405, 'Grief is the price we pay for love.', 65677, 0), (433406, 'The love of a dog is a pure thing. He gives you a trust which is total. You must not betray it.', 1261, 0), (433407, 'If I love you, I show you I love you every day. Little things, big things.', 11331, 0), (433408, 'Friendship may, and often does, grow into love, but love never subsides into friendship.', 62558, 0), (433409, 'Love is a really scary thing, and you never know what''s going to happen. It''s one of the most beautiful things in life, but it''s one of the most terrifying. It''s worth the fear because you have more knowledge, experience, you learn from people, and you have memories.', 52532, 0), (433410, 'When love and skill work together, expect a masterpiece.', 485, 0), (433411, 'Love does not claim possession, but gives freedom.', 430, 0), (433412, 'Love yourself, whatever makes you different, and use it to make you stand out. Mine is my voice and the fact that I''m gay: well, the fact that I''m flamboyantly gay.', 69039, 0), (433413, 'True, we love life, not because we are used to living, but because we are used to loving. There is always some madness in love, but there is also always some reason in madness.', 66050, 0), (433414, 'Life is difficult for everyone; everyone has bad days. Everyone has trouble in their life, because it doesn''t matter how rich you are: Sickness and trouble and worry and love, these things will mess with you at every level of life.', 68286, 0), (433415, 'Family is a unique gift that needs to be appreciated and treasured, even when they''re driving you crazy. As much as they make you mad, interrupt you, annoy you, curse at you, try to control you, these are the people who know you the best and who love you.', 67565, 0), (433416, 'I do not think there is any thrill that can go through the human heart like that felt by the inventor as he sees some creation of the brain unfolding to success... such emotions make a man forget food, sleep, friends, love, everything.', 1908, 0), (433417, 'Our love, our gratitude, our admiration for our men and women in uniform, our veterans and their families - all of that is bigger than any one party or any one election.', 1997, 0), (433418, 'I love my wife and I know she loves me. We''re best friends. We''re just lucky to have found each other. It takes a lot of work but I just feel very blessed that I found the right person. It''s a very fortunate situation and not everyone has that.', 68271, 0), (433419, 'A woman knows the face of the man she loves as a sailor knows the open sea.', 143, 0), (433420, 'I love looking in the mirror and feeling good about what I see.', 69040, 0), (433421, 'Gay marriage - it''s not about two people being gay: it''s about two people who love each other and who have decided to commit to each other for the exact same reasons any other couple would get married.', 69041, 0), (433422, 'To love is to act.', 98, 0), (433423, 'Love will find its way through all languages on its own.', 20453, 0), (433424, 'There is no friendship, no love, like that of the parent for the child.', 2175, 0), (433425, 'Even in the deepest love relationship - when lovers say ''I love you'' to each other - we don''t really know what we''re saying, because language isn''t equal to the complexity of human emotions.', 19769, 0), (433426, 'The best thing about being a DJ is making people happy. There is nothing like seeing people get up from a table to dance or the expression on their face when they hear a song they love. I also love to educate people on music they have never heard.', 69042, 0), (433427, 'Patriotism is love of country. But you can''t love your country without loving your countrymen and countrywomen. We don''t always have to agree, but we must empower each other, we must find the common ground, we must build bridges across our differences to pursue the common good.', 10615, 0), (433428, 'My goal is to be able to provide for myself and not have to worry about the daily expenses. I do want to be able to benefit from my work and make a good living, but I love it so much that I would do it for free.', 69004, 0), (433429, 'People happy in love have an air of intensity.', 952, 0), (433430, 'Love is like a beautiful flower which I may not touch, but whose fragrance makes the garden a place of delight just the same.', 701, 0), (433431, 'And ever has it been known that love knows not its own depth until the hour of separation.', 5542, 0), (433432, 'Football is unconditional love.', 66949, 0), (433433, 'I love being on the road. I love that lifestyle, traveling city to city, rocking out and moving on to the next place.', 69043, 0), (433434, 'Patriotism is not an abstract concept. It begins from one''s own home. It buds out from the love for one''s parents, spouses and children, the love for one''s own home, village and workplace, and further develops into the love for one''s country and fellow people.', 67852, 0), (433435, 'Now, what really makes a teacher is love for the human child; for it is love that transforms the social duty of the educator into the higher consciousness of a mission.', 11408, 0), (433436, 'Wherever the art of medicine is loved, there is also a love of humanity.', 10825, 0), (433437, 'I''m in love with red. I think it''s such a passionate color. Every flag of every country pretty much has red it it. It''s power, there''s no fence sitting with red. Either you love it or you don''t. I think its blood and strength and life. I do love red. I love all colors. Great shades of blue, you find them in nature. They''re all magic.', 10716, 0), (433438, 'I have eclectic taste, and I love vintage style mixed with glamour and old world charm.', 66931, 0), (433439, 'Prayer is an act of love; words are not needed. Even if sickness distracts from thoughts, all that is needed is the will to love.', 69044, 0), (433440, 'But I say to you, Love your enemies and pray for those who persecute you, so that you may be sons of your Father who is in heaven; for he makes his sun rise on the evil and on the good, and sends rain on the just and on the unjust.', 17018, 0), (433441, 'Femininity is not just lipstick, stylish hairdos, and trendy clothes. It is the divine adornment of humanity. It finds expression in your qualities of your capacity to love, your spirituality, delicacy, radiance, sensitivity, creativity, charm, graciousness, gentleness, dignity, and quiet strength.', 9153, 0), (433442, 'With love and patience, nothing is impossible.', 1750, 0), (433443, 'It sounds like a cliche but I also learnt that you''re not going to fall for the right person until you really love yourself and feel good about how you are.', 15748, 0), (433444, 'I love Paris for the million reasons that everybody loves the city. It''s an incredibly romantic and beautiful place.', 31805, 0), (433445, 'But I love Halloween, and I love that feeling: the cold air, the spooky dangers lurking around the corner.', 69045, 0), (433446, 'Whatever possession we gain by our sword cannot be sure or lasting, but the love gained by kindness and moderation is certain and durable.', 7819, 0), (433447, 'True love doesn''t come to you it has to be inside you.', 64247, 0), (433448, 'What I''ve enjoyed most, though, is meeting people who have a real interest in food and sharing ideas with them. Good food is a global thing and I find that there is always something new and amazing to learn - I love it!', 15479, 0), (433449, 'I think it''s not really difficult to write about love. We''ve been saying the same thing over and over for so many years. But it depends on how honest it is and how good you make it feel. You can say ''I love you'' in a trillion ways, and it can always sound different or feel different.', 69046, 0), (433450, 'People confuse ego, lust, insecurity with true love.', 55901, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433451, 'I don''t love studying. I hate studying. I like learning. Learning is beautiful.', 26614, 0), (433452, 'The hunger for love is much more difficult to remove than the hunger for bread.', 70, 0), (433453, 'I love women, but I feel like you can''t trust some of them. Some of them are liars, you know? Like I was in the park and I met this girl, she was cute and she had a dog. And I went up to her, we started talking. She told me her dog''s name. Then I said, ''Does he bite?'' She said, ''No.'' And I said, ''Oh yeah? Then how does he eat?'' Liar.', 2315, 0), (433454, 'The two most misused words in the entire English vocabulary are love and friendship. A true friend would die for you, so when you start trying to count them on one hand, you don''t need any fingers.', 69047, 0), (433455, 'In our life there is a single color, as on an artist''s palette, which provides the meaning of life and art. It is the color of love.', 19806, 0), (433456, 'What can a pencil do for all of us? Amazing things. It can write transcendent poetry, uplifting music, or life-changing equations; it can sketch the future, give life to untold beauty, and communicate the full-force of our love and aspirations.', 50531, 0), (433457, 'You''re imperfect, and you''re wired for struggle, but you are worthy of love and belonging.', 247, 0), (433458, 'Flatter me, and I may not believe you. Criticize me, and I may not like you. Ignore me, and I may not forgive you. Encourage me, and I will not forget you. Love me and I may be forced to love you.', 1820, 0), (433459, 'Let''s practice motivation and love, not discrimination and hate.', 68211, 0), (433460, 'I love the name of honor, more than I fear death.', 62623, 0), (433461, 'The Bible tells us to love our neighbors as ourselves. Surely part of loving in this way is trying to understand what another person wants us to understand. I may not understand perfectly and I may not agree, but if I love you I should try to know what it is you wish I could know.', 18983, 0), (433462, 'No human creature can give orders to love.', 810, 0), (433463, 'A pair of powerful spectacles has sometimes sufficed to cure a person in love.', 11, 0), (433464, 'I''m a basketball player. That''s what I do and what I love but that''s just not all who I am. I''m talented in a lot of different areas.', 1900, 0), (433465, 'I don''t know that love changes. People change. Circumstances change.', 19, 0), (433466, 'I love to be outdoors, so I like to hike, bike and go to the beach.', 69048, 0), (433467, 'I love fairy tales because of their haunting beauty and magical strangeness. They are set in worlds where anything can happen. Frogs can be kings, a thicket of brambles can hide a castle where a royal court has lain asleep for a hundred years, a boy can outwit a giant, and a girl can break a curse with nothing but her courage and steadfastness.', 1906, 0), (433468, 'You are loved just for being who you are, just for existing. You don''t have to do anything to earn it. Your shortcomings, your lack of self-esteem, physical perfection, or social and economic success - none of that matters. No one can take this love away from you, and it will always be here.', 1853, 0), (433469, 'If fear is the great enemy of intimacy, love is its true friend.', 19097, 0), (433470, 'Your competition is not other people but the time you kill, the ill will you create, the knowledge you neglect to learn, the connections you fail to build, the health you sacrifice along the path, your inability to generate ideas, the people around you who don''t support and love your efforts, and whatever god you curse for your bad luck.', 20595, 0), (433471, 'Follow your heart. Do what you love. Because I was constantly struggling with that. If it''s in your heart, go for it. Don''t listen to other people.', 50659, 0), (433472, 'Food, to me, is always about cooking and eating with those you love and care for.', 69049, 0), (433473, 'Your task is not to seek for love, but merely to seek and find all the barriers within yourself that you have built against it.', 20453, 0), (433474, 'I''ve really come to realize you have to love yourself before you can expect someone else to.', 3299, 0), (433475, 'Choose to be kind. Choose to forgive. Let your love grow and shine so that people may look at the example of your life and glorify God in Heaven.', 58655, 0), (433476, 'I love natural beauty, and I think it''s your best look, but I think makeup as an artist is so transformative.', 68466, 0), (433477, 'Our first and last love is self-love.', 6105, 0), (433478, 'A man can be himself only so long as he is alone, and if he does not love solitude, he will not love freedom, for it is only when he is alone that he is really free.', 1304, 0), (433479, 'The Universal Zulu Nation stands to acknowledge wisdom, understanding, freedom, justice, and equality, peace, unity, love, and having fun, work, overcoming the negative through the positive, science, mathematics, faith, facts, and the wonders of God, whether we call him Allah, Jehovah, Yahweh, or Jah.', 69050, 0), (433480, 'True generosity is an offering given freely and out of pure love. No strings attached. No expectations. Time and love are the most valuable possession you can share. ', 10090, 0), (433481, 'Accept yourself, love yourself.', 69051, 0), (433482, 'I want to tell women that you need to love yourself and make yourself a priority. It''s only when you are happy yourself, can you make everyone else around you happy. I am still a dreamer and still believe in fairy tales, but there is only that much one should give another person. You need to keep something for yourself.', 69052, 0), (433483, 'Love is an endless mystery, for it has nothing else to explain it.', 430, 0), (433484, 'I love the beach. I love the sea. All my life I live within - in front of the sea.', 27470, 0), (433485, 'Your duty is to treat everybody with love as a manifestation of the Lord.', 62960, 0), (433486, 'Love in the real world means saying you''re sorry 10 times a day.', 34737, 0), (433487, 'All things on earth point home in old October; sailors to sea, travellers to walls and fences, hunters to field and hollow and the long voice of the hounds, the lover to the love he has forsaken.', 1971, 0), (433488, 'I love being my husband''s wife.', 69053, 0), (433489, 'Love is not to be purchased, and affection has no price.', 62829, 0), (433490, 'Drawing is the only thing I''ve found in which I can lose myself completely. I love it. It started as something that relaxed me, but now it''s a struggle because I''m pushing myself. The day-to-day sketching is fraught.', 67557, 0), (433491, 'Don''t threaten me with love, baby. Let''s just go walking in the rain.', 9623, 0), (433492, 'I don''t think of myself as a role model. I do try to live in a compassionate, considerate and positive way. The only advice I can offer is to find what you love to do, find the joy in it, and express yourself through your passion.', 69054, 0), (433493, 'Through Love all that is bitter will be sweet, Through Love all that is copper will be gold, Through Love all dregs will become wine, through Love all pain will turn to medicine.', 20453, 0), (433494, 'The purest and most thoughtful minds are those which love colour the most.', 485, 0), (433495, 'I''m very happy being me, although sometimes I''d love to be a bird so that I could fly.', 30202, 0), (433496, 'All major religious traditions carry basically the same message, that is love, compassion and forgiveness the important thing is they should be part of our daily lives.', 5025, 0), (433497, 'To say ''I love you'' one must first be able to say the ''I.''', 631, 0), (433498, 'I think it''s part of my personality - I love to travel I love different cultures and philosophies and perspectives on things. ', 69055, 0), (433499, 'Love is that condition in which the happiness of another person is essential to your own... Jealousy is a disease, love is a healthy condition. The immature mind often mistakes one for the other, or assumes that the greater the love, the greater the jealousy.', 17, 0), (433500, 'The secret to a happy marriage is if you can be at peace with someone within four walls, if you are content because the one you love is near to you, either upstairs or downstairs, or in the same room, and you feel that warmth that you don''t find very often, then that is what love is all about.', 68967, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433501, 'Food brings people together on many different levels. It''s nourishment of the soul and body it''s truly love. ', 66406, 0), (433502, 'It is sad not to love, but it is much sadder not to be able to love.', 1504, 0), (433503, 'If you don''t love me, it does not matter, anyway I can love for both of us.', 952, 0), (433504, 'I hate losing and cricket being my first love, once I enter the ground it''s a different zone altogether and that hunger for winning is always there.', 5213, 0), (433505, 'Fall in love with a dog, and in many ways you enter a new orbit, a universe that features not just new colors but new rituals, new rules, a new way of experiencing attachment.', 18166, 0), (433506, 'Love has no age, no limit; and no death.', 5359, 0), (433507, 'The love of heaven makes one heavenly.', 13, 0), (433508, 'I must learn to love the fool in me - the one who feels too much, talks too much, takes too many chances, wins sometimes and loses often, lacks self-control, loves and hates, hurts and gets hurt, promises and breaks promises, laughs and cries.', 65610, 0), (433509, 'Falling in love and having a relationship are two different things.', 61050, 0), (433510, 'Win, lose or draw, you''re all my cousins and I love you.', 69056, 0), (433511, 'The best portion of a good man''s life is his little, nameless, unremembered acts of kindness and of love.', 2063, 0), (433512, 'To all the other dreamers out there, don''t ever stop or let the world''s negativity disenchant you or your spirit. If you surround yourself with love and the right people, anything is possible.', 69057, 0), (433513, 'Surround yourself with people who provide you with support and love and remember to give back as much as you can in return.', 69058, 0), (433514, 'At the center of non-violence stands the principle of love.', 21767, 0), (433515, 'I love walking down the street and seeing faces and drama and happiness and sadness and dirt and cleanliness.', 68578, 0), (433516, 'The struggle of my life created empathy - I could relate to pain, being abandoned, having people not love me.', 588, 0), (433517, 'Mental prayer in my opinion is nothing else than an intimate sharing between friends it means taking time frequently to be alone with Him who we know loves us. The important thing is not to think much but to love much and so do that which best stirs you to love. Love is not great delight but desire to please God in everything. ', 69044, 0), (433518, 'Flowers are an easy, eloquent expression of love at a time when words can seem clumsy and inadequate.', 9037, 0), (433519, 'The body of a beautiful woman is not made for love it is too exquisite. ', 69059, 0), (433520, 'Nothing can bring a real sense of security into the home except true love.', 4008, 0), (433521, 'Love has reasons which reason cannot understand.', 144, 0), (433522, 'If we love our country, we should also love our countrymen.', 1727, 0), (433523, 'Love is life. And if you miss love, you miss life.', 406, 0), (433524, 'Thank you, dear God, for this good life and forgive us if we do not love it enough. Thank you for the rain. And for the chance to wake up in three hours and go fishing: I thank you for that now, because I won''t feel so thankful then.', 1205, 0), (433525, 'I do not want a husband who honours me as a queen, if he does not love me as a woman.', 1401, 0), (433526, 'I love the crowds at festivals because they''re so chilled out.', 47040, 0), (433527, 'Affection is responsible for nine-tenths of whatever solid and durable happiness there is in our lives.', 26, 0), (433528, 'Even when I''m sick and depressed, I love life.', 2523, 0), (433529, 'As long as you know yourself and you got good people around you and you passionate about what you do, that''s all that matters because at the end of the day, you go to sleep with the people you love, you wake up with the people you love, and you spend your time with the people you love.', 69060, 0), (433530, 'When you lose a person you love so much, surviving the loss is difficult.', 5874, 0), (433531, 'Times of transition are strenuous, but I love them. They are an opportunity to purge, rethink priorities, and be intentional about new habits. We can make our new normal any way we want.', 12208, 0), (433532, 'I love life. I wish I could live another 500 years, truly. There is so much to do. I don''t feel bitter or angry or disappointed. If anything, I am very grateful for where I come from. I have absolutely no regrets.', 69061, 0), (433533, 'Love does not consist in gazing at each other, but in looking outward together in the same direction.', 69, 0), (433534, 'I love America more than any other country in this world, and, exactly for this reason, I insist on the right to criticize her perpetually.', 67562, 0), (433535, 'There have to be reasons that you get up in the morning and you want to live. Why do you want to live? What''s the point? What inspires you? What do you love about the future? If the future does not include being out there among the stars and being a multi-planet species, I find that incredibly depressing.', 10864, 0), (433536, 'The best proof of love is trust.', 5478, 0), (433537, 'I don''t stress myself about my looks. I love to laugh. I like being able to lead an interesting life.', 47394, 0), (433538, 'I''m just not into trying to convince people like me. I always say to myself, ''It is what it is.'' I walk into a situation knowing that people are either going to love me or they''re not, and that''s OK. I''m just going to be me. You can''t be everything to everyone.', 69062, 0), (433539, 'If a relationship is going wrong, if a marriage is going wrong, the answer cannot simply be to say, ''You can''t afford to break up because you are going to lose the house.'' The answer has to be only one thing, which is ''I love you.''', 17562, 0), (433540, 'I love, but I am not entirely sure how to be loved: how to be seen and known for the utterly flawed woman I am. It demands surrender. It demands acknowledging that I am not perfect, but perhaps I deserve affection anyway.', 9530, 0), (433541, 'If you want a love message to be heard, it has got to be sent out. To keep a lamp burning, we have to keep putting oil in it.', 70, 0), (433542, 'Love is the greatest refreshment in life.', 981, 0), (433543, 'I think what it takes to succeed remains the same. You have to have a real love of your sport to carry you through all the bad times, you still want to go ski even when things aren''t working. You must have a commitment to work hard and to never give up.', 69063, 0), (433544, 'Knowledge is love and light and vision.', 701, 0), (433545, 'What I''m not confused about is the world needing much more love, no hate, no prejudice, no bigotry and more unity, peace and understanding. Period.', 2141, 0), (433546, 'Love is a friendship set to music.', 1123, 0), (433547, 'Only divine love bestows the keys of knowledge.', 606, 0), (433548, 'When we focus on our gratitude, the tide of disappointment goes out and the tide of love rushes in.', 12208, 0), (433549, 'I like to think I''m a pretty good friend. I love having a good time, and I enjoy being able to share those good times with others.', 69064, 0), (433550, 'I love meeting new people I think everyone has a story to tell. We should all listen sometimes. ', 69065, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433551, 'Do all things with love.', 1369, 0), (433552, 'A coward is incapable of exhibiting love it is the prerogative of the brave. ', 32, 0), (433553, 'Treasure the love you receive above all. It will survive long after your good health has vanished.', 1369, 0), (433554, 'To love our neighbor as ourselves is such a truth for regulating human society, that by that alone one might determine all the cases in social morality.', 2375, 0), (433555, 'Gaming has been a great way to get to know people. That''s part of what I love about games, that they are social.', 69066, 0), (433556, 'I love you all too much, it''s one of just of my problems.', 69067, 0), (433557, 'I love the beach, and I love sunshine.', 69068, 0), (433558, 'Beauty, sweet love, is like the morning dew, Whose short refresh upon tender green, Cheers for a time, but till the sun doth show And straight is gone, as it had never been.', 69069, 0), (433559, 'Do what you love. Know your own bone; gnaw at it, bury it, unearth it, and gnaw it still.', 1049, 0), (433560, 'New Age values are conscious evolution, a non-sectarian society, a non-military culture, global sharing, healing the environment, sustainable economies, self-determination, social justice, economic empowerment of the poor, love, compassion in action, going beyond religious fundamentalism, going beyond nationalism-extreme nationalism, culture.', 1194, 0), (433561, 'My mom always said that there would be haters. Not everyone can love ya.', 22751, 0), (433562, 'Rocks and waters, etc., are words of God, and so are men. We all flow from one fountain Soul. All are expressions of one Love.', 1402, 0), (433563, 'Love is something far more than desire for sexual intercourse it is the principal means of escape from the loneliness which afflicts most men and women throughout the greater part of their lives. ', 95, 0), (433564, 'The eyes those silent tongues of love.', 62284, 0), (433565, 'We have gone through some difficult times like everyone else and perhaps our working together and respecting each other''s abilities, in addition to that little thing called love, helped us survive.', 69070, 0), (433566, 'I love when people underestimate me and then become pleasantly surprised.', 34530, 0), (433567, 'I love argument, I love debate. I don''t expect anyone just to sit there and agree with me, that''s not their job.', 1945, 0), (433568, 'I''ve always believed fitness is an entry point to help you build that happier, healthier life. When your health is strong, you''re capable of taking risks. You''ll feel more confident to ask for the promotion. You''ll have more energy to be a better mom. You''ll feel more deserving of love.', 1860, 0), (433569, 'The good in this world far outweighs the evil. Our common humanity transcends our differences, and our most effective response to terror is compassion, it''s unity, and it''s love.', 69071, 0), (433570, 'A good youth ought to have a fear of God, to be subject to his parents, to give honor to his elders, to preserve his purity; he ought not to despise humility, but should love forbearance and modesty. All these are an ornament to youthful years.', 69072, 0), (433571, 'Love and friendship exclude each other.', 5879, 0), (433572, 'I feel that there is nothing more truly artistic than to love people.', 89, 0), (433573, 'The ultimate dream in life is to be able to do what you love and learn something from it.', 2549, 0), (433574, 'I love going to coffee shops and just sitting and listening.', 69073, 0), (433575, 'It''s hard asking someone with a broken heart to fall in love again.', 24560, 0), (433576, 'If you do not love me I shall not be loved If I do not love you I shall not love.', 1084, 0), (433577, 'For small creatures such as we the vastness is bearable only through love.', 133, 0), (433578, 'Some white people hate black people, and some white people love black people, some black people hate white people, and some black people love white people. So you see it''s not an issue of black and white, it''s an issue of Lovers and Haters.', 69074, 0), (433579, 'The moment I first heard love I gave up my soul, my heart, and my eyes.', 20453, 0), (433580, 'Love is a portion of the soul itself, and it is of the same nature as the celestial breathing of the atmosphere of paradise.', 98, 0), (433581, 'Dost thou love life? Then do not squander time, for that is the stuff life is made of.', 1077, 0), (433582, 'I can''t explain chemistry. I really can''t. I haven''t got a clue what it''s all about. It just happens. It''s like falling in love. You can''t explain why you fall in love or explain why it''s this particular person.', 56664, 0), (433583, 'Love places someone else in the centre of your being and your own self is blurred.', 5980, 0), (433584, 'If equal affection cannot be, let the more loving be me.', 219, 0), (433585, 'A youth, when at home, should be filial and, abroad, respectful to his elders. He should be earnest and truthful. He should overflow in love to all and cultivate the friendship of the good. When he has time and opportunity, after the performance of these things, he should employ them in polite studies.', 819, 0), (433586, 'I think good things are happening to me and will continue. I am not optimistic about the rest of the species, but I''m so blessed, it''s almost scary. I''m sorry to disappoint you, but I have a wildly sunny disposition. I love to laugh.', 28955, 0), (433587, 'The love of husband and wife, which is creative of new human life, is a marvellously personal sharing in the creative love of God who brings into being the eternal soul that comes to every human being with the gift of human life.', 69075, 0), (433588, 'He that is jealous is not in love.', 63060, 0), (433589, 'People love me. And you know what, I have been very successful. Everybody loves me.', 64643, 0), (433590, 'I think tolerance and acceptance and love is something that feeds every community.',