emory, the stronger and stranger it is.', 76, 0), (433844, 'The ear is the avenue to the heart.', 808, 0), (433845, 'Love seeketh not itself to please, nor for itself hath any care, but for another gives its ease, and builds a Heaven in Hell''s despair.', 221, 0), (433846, 'The love of liberty is the love of others the love of power is the love of ourselves. ', 8948, 0), (433847, 'Follow love and it will flee, flee love and it will follow thee.', 31023, 0), (433848, 'Romantic love is an illusion. Most of us discover this truth at the end of a love affair or else when the sweet emotions of love lead us into marriage and then turn down their flames.', 790, 0), (433849, 'To be able to say how much love, is love but little.', 66050, 0), (433850, 'One does not fall in love; one grows into love, and love grows in him.', 924, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433851, 'Love is a great beautifier.', 296, 0), (433852, 'The fate of love is that it always seems too little or too much.', 62313, 0), (433853, 'Love is the great miracle cure. Loving ourselves works miracles in our lives.', 5296, 0), (433854, 'For above all things Love means sweetness, and truth, and measure; yea, loyalty to the loved one and to your word. And because of this I dare not meddle with so high a matter.', 9910, 0), (433855, 'There is no person that love cannot heal there is no soul that love cannot save. ', 62159, 0), (433856, 'When love is at its best, one loves so much that he cannot forget.', 25904, 0), (433857, 'It''s important for us to latch onto the people that we love.', 69095, 0), (433858, 'Love can be unselfish, in the sense of being benevolent and generous, without being selfless.', 69091, 0), (433859, 'Love knows not distance it hath no continent its eyes are for the stars. ', 68771, 0), (433860, 'The essential conditions of everything you do must be choice, love, passion.', 44758, 0), (433861, 'I love California, I practically grew up in Phoenix.', 17186, 0), (433862, 'I used to think that love was giving up everything of yourself and giving it to the other person. Now, I''ve realized that love is when you have somebody that doesn''t make you give up half of yourself.', 69096, 0), (433863, 'Your feelings so are important to write down, to capture, and to remember because today you''re heartbroken, but tomorrow you''ll be in love again.', 100, 0), (433864, 'Have we not come to such an impasse in the modern world that we must love our enemies - or else? The chain reaction of evil - hate begetting hate, wars producing more wars - must be broken, or else we shall be plunged into the dark abyss of annihilation.', 21767, 0), (433865, 'Happy is the man whom the Muses love: sweet speech flows from his mouth.', 3287, 0), (433866, 'We have observed that, in society and the world in which we live, selfishness has increased more than love for others, and that men of good will must work, each with his own strengths and expertise, to ensure that love for others increases until it is equal and possibly exceeds love for oneself.', 6248, 0), (433867, 'To put yourself in another''s place requires real imagination, but by doing so each Girl Scout will be able to love among others happily.', 69097, 0), (433868, 'Cherish sunsets, wild creatures and wild places. Have a love affair with the wonder and beauty of the earth.', 69098, 0), (433869, 'I love this life. I feel like I am always catching my breath and saying, ''Oh! Will you look at that?'' Photography has been my way of bearing witness to the joy I find in seeing the extraordinary in ordinary life. You don''t look for pictures. Your pictures are looking for you.', 69099, 0), (433870, 'There is nothing wrong with America that faith, love of freedom, intelligence, and energy of her citizens cannot cure.', 2119, 0), (433871, 'You protect your being when you love yourself better. That''s the secret.', 69100, 0), (433872, 'When people get married because they think it''s a long-time love affair, they''ll be divorced very soon, because all love affairs end in disappointment. But marriage is a recognition of a spiritual identity.', 1123, 0), (433873, 'Love, whether newly born, or aroused from a deathlike slumber, must always create sunshine, filling the heart so full of radiance, this it overflows upon the outward world.', 650, 0), (433874, 'I represent the kids who come from nothing but who understand it all and love it all. That''s what I represent - those are the cool kids, you know, the kids of tomorrow, because who would''ve known that I''d be who I am today? We are the kids of tomorrow.', 66683, 0), (433875, 'Love is stronger than justice.', 9151, 0), (433876, 'There is no limit to the power of loving.', 36156, 0), (433877, 'Love dies only when growth stops.', 442, 0), (433878, 'It is an extra dividend when you like the girl you''ve fallen in love with.', 62620, 0), (433879, 'I have been married twice, and those were not the happiest times of my life. Part of the problem, quite frankly, is that when you get married, the romance disappears and the children arrive and the love is transferred. It shouldn''t be that way, but too often it is transferred to the children.', 38121, 0), (433880, 'Love is only a dirty trick played on us to achieve continuation of the species.', 235, 0), (433881, 'Teach love, generosity, good manners and some of that will drift from the classroom to the home and who knows, the children will be educating the parents.', 67012, 0), (433882, 'I love history, doesn''t matter what era, I''m fascinated.', 21291, 0), (433883, 'I suffer the mortification of seeing myself attacked right and left by people at home professing patriotism and love of country who never heard the whistle of a hostile bullet. I pity them and the nation dependent on such for its existence. I am thankful, however that, though such people make a great noise, the masses are not like them.', 9689, 0), (433884, 'To fear love is to fear life, and those who fear life are already three parts dead.', 95, 0), (433885, 'My love of fine art increased - the more of it I saw, the more of it I wanted to see.', 11793, 0), (433886, 'Success is when you see something, and you say, ''I want to do that,'' and then you do it. It''s being happy with what you do and doing what you love every day.', 68914, 0), (433887, 'I''m a photographer, period. I love photography, the immediacy of it. I like the craft, the idea of saying ''I''m a photographer.''', 69101, 0), (433888, 'We love but once, for once only are we perfectly equipped for loving.', 9518, 0), (433889, 'One''s art goes as far and as deep as one''s love goes.', 19790, 0), (433890, 'One word frees us of all the weight and pain in life. That word is love.', 139, 0), (433891, 'At the touch of love everyone becomes a poet.', 51, 0), (433892, 'There are never enough I Love You''s.', 2212, 0), (433893, 'We may give without loving, but we cannot love without giving.', 15421, 0), (433894, 'Love, having no geography, knows no boundaries.', 262, 0), (433895, 'Love prefers twilight to daylight.', 24754, 0), (433896, 'Love is the only reality and it is not a mere sentiment. It is the ultimate truth that lies at the heart of creation.', 430, 0), (433897, 'Gestures, in love, are incomparably more attractive, effective and valuable than words.', 1013, 0), (433898, 'Love is energy of life.', 698, 0), (433899, 'Who would give a law to lovers? Love is unto itself a higher law.', 3096, 0), (433900, 'Love him and let him love you. Do you think anything else under heaven really matters?', 67562, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (433901, 'There is always something left to love. And if you ain''t learned that, you ain''t learned nothing.', 4386, 0), (433902, 'The god of love lives in a state of need. It is a need. It is an urge. It is a homeostatic imbalance. Like hunger and thirst, it''s almost impossible to stamp out.', 51, 0), (433903, 'Love is not only something you feel, it is something you do.', 9165, 0), (433904, 'The sweetest noise on earth, a woman''s tongue; A string which hath no discord.', 69102, 0), (433905, 'Love is the difficult realization that something other than oneself is real.', 210, 0), (433906, 'Familiar acts are beautiful through love.', 165, 0), (433907, 'The highest function of love is that it makes the loved one a unique and irreplacable being.', 105, 0), (433908, 'No, there''s nothing half so sweet in life as love''s young dream.', 790, 0), (433909, 'Love is the greatest gift that God has given us. It''s free.', 69103, 0), (433910, 'Who ever loved that loved not at first sight?', 6093, 0), (433911, 'Absence - that common cure of love.', 62558, 0), (433912, 'Love is being stupid together.', 3087, 0), (433913, 'There is room in the smallest cottage for a happy loving pair.', 1988, 0), (433914, 'A kiss is a rosy dot over the ''i'' of loving.', 34733, 0), (433915, 'There is only one kind of love, but there are a thousand imitations.', 154, 0), (433916, 'Love comes unseen we only see it go. ', 12929, 0), (433917, 'The fact is that love is of two kinds, one which commands, and one which obeys. The two are quite distinct, and the passion to which the one gives rise is not the passion of the other.', 143, 0), (433918, 'Is it not by love alone that we succeed in penetrating to the very essence of being?', 16868, 0), (433919, 'The praise that comes from love does not make us vain, but more humble.', 64116, 0), (433920, 'Loved. You can''t use it in the past tense. Death does not stop that love at all.', 1601, 0), (433